of 258, which led to the persecution of the Christians. 262 is the year that the Heruls accompanied the Goths ravaging the coasts of the Black Sea and the Aegean. 263 is the year that the Wei Kingdom conquers the kingdom of Shu Han, one of the Chinese Three Kingdoms. 264 is the year that Jiang Wei tries to restore the Kingdom of Shu by persuading Zhong Hui to declare a rebellion against Sima Zhao, ruler of Cao Wei. 265 is the year that Jin Wudi becomes ruler of part of China, beginning the Jin Dynasty. 266 is the year that the rule of High King Cormac mac Airt ends (approximate date). 267 is the year that Aureolus, charged with defending Italy, defeats Victorinus (co-emperor of Gaul), is proclaimed emperor by his troops, and begins his march on Rome. 268 is the year that Marcus Aurelius Claudius is charged by the Senate for having murdered Gallienus (it will never be proven). 269 is the year that Claudius II travels to Sirmium and prepares a war against the Vandals, who raid Pannonia. 270 is the year that the Romans leave Utrecht after regular invasions of Germanic tribes. 271 is the year that Victorinus, Emperor of the Gallic Empire, is assassinated by Attitianus, reportedly for reasons of personal revenge. 272 is the year that Paul of Samosata is deposed as Patriarch of Antioch. 273 is the year that Cassius Longinus, counselor of queen Zenobia, is executed by the Romans for conspiring against Aurelian. 274 is the year that the Kingdom of Aksum attains great prosperity thanks to its control of Red Sea trade. 275 is the year that Marcus Claudius Tacitus is proclaimed Emperor by the Senate, his half brother Marcus Annius Florianus becomes Praetorian Prefect on September 25th. 276 is the year that Reign of Mahasena in Ceylon. 277 is the year that Tuoba Xilu succeeds his father Tuoba Liwei as chieftain of the Tuoba clan. 278 is the year that Emperor Probus defeats the Alamanni, advancing through the Neckar valley. 279 is the year that Emperor Probus defeats the Burgundians and Vandals in Raetia and Pannonia (modern Switzerland and Hungary). 280 is the year that Probus defeats the army under Bonosus, he sees no way out and hangs himself. 281 is the year that Emperor Probus returns to Rome, where he celebrates his triumph over the Vandals and the usurpers (Bonosus, Julius Saturninus and Proculus). 282 is the year that the Patriarch Theonas of Alexandria becomes one of the first bishops to use the title Pope. 283 is the year that Carus dies in mysterious circumstances during an expedition against the Sassanids, during a violent dust storm he is killed by a stroke of lightning. 284 is the year that Diocletianus advanced with his army across the Balkans on Winter NaNth. 285 is the year that Carausius, naval commander at Bononia (modern Boulogne), is given the task to clear the English Channel of Frankish and Saxon pirates. 286 is the year that Tuoba Chuo succeeds his brother Tuoba Xilu as chieftain of the Tuoba clan. 287 is the year that Emperor Diocletian and Maximian become Roman Consuls. 288 is the year that Emperor Diocletian conducts a military campaign in Raetia (Switzerland). 289 is the year that Emperor Diocletian gains several victories along the Danube against the Sarmatians. 290 is the year that Carausius begins to build a series of fortifications on the Saxon Shore in south-east England. 291 is the year that Emperor Diocletian signs peace treaties with the kingdoms of Aksum and Nubia. 292 is the year that Achilleus, Roman general, is proclaimed emperor in Alexandria. 293 is the year that Emperor Diocletian and Maximian appoint Constantius Chlorus and Galerius as Caesars on March 1st. 294 is the year that Emperor Diocletian goes with the young Constantine I the Great (later the first Christian Roman Emperor) on his staff to Egypt. 295 is the year that Galerius, Roman Caesar in the Balkan, is dispatched to Egypt to fight against the rebellious cities Busiris and Coptos. 296 is the year that Constantius Chlorus assembles two invasion fleets with the intent of crossing the English Channel. 297 is the year that Emperor Maximian begins a offensive against the Berbers in Mauritania, driving them back into their homelands in the Atlas Mountains. 298 is the year that Emperor Maximian concludes his campaign in North Africa against the Berbers, and makes a triumphal entry into Carthage on March 10th. 299 is the year that Galerius commissions the Arch of Galerius in Thessaloniki (Greece).

300 is the year that the elephant becomes extinct in North Africa (approximate date). 301 is the year that the republic of San Marino is established (traditional date) on September 3rd. 302 is the year that Emperor Diocletian begins passing laws against Christians and a policy of religious oppression in Antioch. 303 is the year that the Triumphal Arch of Maximian is erected in Salonica. 304 is the year that Sichuan earns its independence from China. 305 is the year that Constantius Chlorus and Galerius are declared Augusti; Flavius Valerius Severus and Maximinus II Daia are appointed Caesars. 306 is the year that Basilica of Maxentius and Constantine (Basilica Nova), Rome, is started to be built. 307 is the year that Severus II is captured and imprisoned at Tres Tabernae on September 16th. 308 is the year that Kingdom of Xiongnu established in northern China. 309 is the year that the Spanish provinces revolt from the control of Maxentius, acknowledging Constantine the Great as their Emperor. 310 is the year that Pope Eusebius exiled to Sicily died from a hunger strike. 311 is the year that the Donatist schism occurs in the African church. 312 is the year that Constantine I Addresses the People in the Roman Forum, sculptural relief on the Arch of Constantine, Rome, is made on C. 312–315 NaNth. 313 is the year that Basilica of Maxentius and Constantine (Basilica Nova), Rome, is finished. 314 is the year that Pope Sylvester I succeeds Pope Miltiades as the 33rd pope on January 31st. 315 is the year that Constantine the Great and co-emperor Licinius battle the Sarmates, the Goths and the Carpians along the Danube. 316 is the year that Emperor Constantine the Great issues an edict prohibiting the punishment of slaves by crucifixion and facial branding. 317 is the year that Emperor Constantine the Great and co-emperor Licinius elevate their sons Crispus, Constantine II (being still an baby) and Licinius II to Caesars on March 1st. 318 is the year that Gregory the Illuminator appoints his son Aristax as successor in the patriarchate of Armenia. 319 is the year that Emperor Constantine the Great prohibits the separation of the families of slaves during a change in ownership. 320 is the year that December 25 is introduced as the birthday of Jesus. 321 is the year that Calcidius translates Plato into Latin. 322 is the year that the first dependable representation of a horse rider with paired stirrups was found in China in a Jin Dynasty tomb (China). 323 is the year that Crown Prince Jin Mingdi succeeds Jin Yuandi as emperor of the Eastern Jin Dynasty. 324 is the year that Licinius abdicates his position as Emperor on December 19th. 325 is the year that the Church of the Nativity is built in Bethlehem. 326 is the year that Fausta, second wife of Constantine I, is also executed. 327 is the year that Old St. Peter's Basilica, Rome, is finished. 328 is the year that Alexandria's patriarch Bishop Alexander dies and is succeeded by his deacon Athanasius on May 9th. 329 is the year that the Han Zhao dynasty, a Southern Xiongnu state during the Sixteen Kingdoms, ends. 330 is the year that the Bible is translated into the Gothic language by Wulfila. 331 is the year that Eusebius of Caesarea writes the Onomasticon. 332 is the year that Constantine I constructs a bridge across the Danube in order to increase trade between the Visigoths and Rome. 333 is the year that Emperor Constantine the Great pulls back Roman troops out of Britain and abandoned work on the Hadrian's Wall. 334 is the year that Emperor Constantine the Great reauthorises gladiatorial combat. 335 is the year that Flavius Dalmatius is raised to the rank of Caesar, with control of Thracia and Macedonia on September 19th. 336 is the year that the first recorded customs tariff is in use in Palmyra. 337 is the year that Shapur II besieged the Roman fortress of Nisibis (Syria), but is repulsed by the forces under Lucilianus. 338 is the year that Emperor Constantius II intervenes against the Persians in Armenia. 339 is the year that Eusebius of Nicomedia is made bishop of Constantinople while another Arian succeeds Athanasius as bishop of Alexandria under the name Gregory. 340 is the year that Wulfila spreads evangelism among the Goths for 7 years. 341 is the year that Paul I is restored as Patriarch of Constantinople. 342 is the year that Paul I, Patriarch of Constantinople, is deposed and replaced by Macedonius I. 343 is the year that Emperor Constantius II invades Adiabene, a vassal kingdom of Armenia (Persian Empire). 344 is the year that Bishop Eustorgius I brings relics of the Three Magi from Constantinople to Milan, according to a 12th century legend. 345 is the year that the merchant Knai Thomman visits the Malabar Coast in Kerala (India) and assists the church there. 346 is the year that Emperor Constans I uses his influence to secure the return of Athanasius. 347 is the year that the Council of Philippopolis is held as the result of Eastern bishops leaving the Council of Sardica. 348 is the year that nothing interesting came to pass. 349 is the year that the Mou-jong (proto-Mongols) take control of North China. 350 is the year that Vetranio meets Constantius II at Naissus (Serbia) and assembled the troops on December 25th. 351 is the year that the Jewish revolt against Gallus breaks out on May 7th. 352 is the year that Constantius Gallus sends his general (magister equitum) Ursicinus to forcefully put down the Jewish revolt in Palestine. 353 is the year that Wang Xizhi, Chinese calligrapher, produces "Preface to the Poems Composed at the Orchid Pavilion" in running script style. 354 is the year that Fu Sheng, emperor of the Former Qin, reigns in northern China. 355 is the year that Arbitio and Lollianus Mavortius begin their term as Roman consuls on January 1st. 356 is the year that Naemul becomes king of the Silla dynasty (Three Kingdoms of Korea). 357 is the year that Emperor Constantius II enters Rome for the first time to celebrate his victory over Magnentius on April 28th. 358 is the year that Emperor Constantius II builds new forts to secure upper Mesopotamia. 359 is the year that Sarcophagus of Junius Bassus, in the Old St. Peter's Basilica, Vatican, is made (approximate date). 360 is the year that Japan begins 30-year period of great influence in Korea. 361 is the year that Gregory Nazianzus, (Saint Gregory the Theologian), returns to Nazianzus and becomes a priest by his father. 362 is the year that an earthquake strikes Nicaea (Turkey). 363 is the year that Emperor Julian departs from Antioch with his army (90,000 men) and heads north towards the Euphrates on March 5th. 364 is the year that Emperor Jovian dies after a reign of eight months on February 17th. 365 is the year that Procopius revolts and bribes two legions passing by Constantinople on September 28th. 366 is the year that the Alamanni cross the frozen Rhine in large numbers, and invade the Gallic provinces on January 2nd. 367 is the year that Epiphanius of Salamis becomes bishop of Salamis, Cyprus. 368 is the year that an earthquake strikes Nicaea (Turkey). 369 is the year that Emperor Valens crosses the Danube at Noviodunum (Romania), and attacks the Gothic tribes (Greuthungi and Tervingi) on Spring NaNth. 370 is the year that Athanaric, Gothic leader of the Tervingi, advanced eastwards and takes up a defensive position along the banks of the Dniester (Romania). 371 is the year that the neo-Persian Empire attains the zenith of its power under king Shapur II as the Romans renew their war against Persia. 372 is the year that Jin Xiaowudi, age 10, succeeds his father Jin Jianwendi on September 12th. 373 is the year that Saint Martin of Tours undertakes the Christianization of Gaul. 374 is the year that Spearthrower Owl ascends to the throne and becomes ruler of Teotihuacan (Mexico) on May 4th. 375 is the year that the first two Korean Buddhist temples are built. 376 is the year that Lupicinus, Comes (Count) of Thrace, tries to bring the Visigoths back under control. 377 is the year that Emperor Valens requests his nephew Gratian to send Roman troops against the Goths. 378 is the year that the Goths with their wagons and families vulnerable to attack, withdraw back to the north. 379 is the year that Gregory Nazianzus becomes Patriarch of Constantinople, and is wounded when he is attacked by a mob of heretics. 380 is the year that the Council of Saragossa is held; Spanish and Aquitanian bishops condemn the teachings of Priscillianism. 381 is the year that the Visigothic chieftain Athanaric becomes the first foreign king to visit the East Roman capital of Constantinople. 382 is the year that the same council adopts Trinitarianism as orthodoxy, condemning Apollinarism. 383 is the year that Niall of the Nine Hostages becomes the first High King of Ireland. 384 is the year that an edict of Theodosius I closes pagan temples in the Nile Valley (Egypt). 385 is the year that Copper extraction and casting begins in the mines of Kansanshi in southernmost Africa, at the border of Zaire and Zambia. 386 is the year that a column is constructed at Constantinople in honour of Theodosius I. Reliefs depict the emperor's victory over the "barbarians" in the Balkan. 387 is the year that the widowed emperor Theodosius I takes Valentinian II in protection and marries his sister Flavia Galla on Winter NaNth. 388 is the year that Paternus becomes bishop of the Episcopal see of Braga (Portugal). 389 is the year that all pagan buildings in Alexandria, including the library, are destroyed by fire. 390 is the year that the Visigoths and Huns, led by Alaric, invade Thrace. 391 is the year that Quintus Aurelius Symmachus, urban prefect of Rome, pleads for traditional cult practices. 392 is the year that Theodosius I becomes the last emperor who rules the whole Roman Empire. 393 is the year that Emperor Theodosius I proclaims his son Honorius, age 8, co-ruler (Augustus) of the Western Roman Empire on January 23rd. 394 is the year that the Council of Bagaï in Africa brings 310 Donatist bishops together. 395 is the year that Augustine, age 40, becomes bishop of Hippo Regius (modern Algeria). 396 is the year that Emperor Jin Andi, age 14, succeeds his father Jin Xiaowudi as ruler of the Eastern Jin Dynasty. 397 is the year that Sulpicius Severus writes the earliest biography of Martin of Tours, the first known "life of a saint" ever written. 398 is the year that Emperor Honorius marries, in quick succession, Stilicho's daughter Maria. 399 is the year that Gainas, a Gothic leader, is made magister militum and forms an alliance with deserters of Tribigild along the Bosphorus.

400 is the year that Richu, the eldest son of Nintoku, becomes the 17th emperor of Japan. 401 is the year that Emperor Arcadius sends many gifts to the Hunnish chieftain Uldin in appreciation of his victory over the Goths and Gainas. 402 is the year that the Visigoths advance on Mediolanum (modern Milan) and laid siege to Asti in Liguria. 403 is the year that Hui Yuan argues that Buddhist monks should be exempt from bowing to the emperor. 404 is the year that Gwanggaeto the Great of Goguryeo (Korea) attacks Liaodong and takes the entire Liaodong Peninsula. 405 is the year that the Khitan are first mentioned in Chinese chronicles. 406 is the year that Stained glass is used for the first time in churches in Rome. 407 is the year that Liu Bobo (Xia Wuliedi) founds the state of Xia and claims the title "Heavenly Prince" (Tian Wang). 408 is the year that Attila, age 12, is sent as child hostage to the court at Rome and in return, the Romans sent Flavius Aetius to the Huns. 409 is the year that the Vandals, led by king Gunderic, cross the Pyrenees into the Iberian Peninsula on October 13th. 410 is the year that Flavius Constantius, Roman general and politician, is promoted to the rank of magister militum. 411 is the year that the Conference of Carthage on donatism. 412 is the year that Heraclianus, governor (Comes Africae), revolts against Honorius and proclaimed himself Augustus. 413 is the year that Heraclianus, Roman usurper, lands in Italy with a large army to fight emperor Honorius. 414 is the year that Galla Placidia, half-sister of emperor Honorius, is married to the Visigothic king Ataulf at Narbonne on January 1st. 415 is the year that the Daysan River floods Edessa (Mesopotamia) on March 18th. 416 is the year that the Visigoths continue their invasion of Hispania and take control of Tarraconensis. 417 is the year that the Visigoths are granted Aquitaine, and become allies (foederati) of the Western Roman Empire. 418 is the year that Emperor Honorius bribes Wallia, king of the Visigoths, into regaining Hispania for the Roman Empire. 419 is the year that Jin Gongdi, age 33, succeeds his developmentally disabled brother Jin Andi as emperor of the Eastern Jin Dynasty. 420 is the year that the Southern Dynasties begin in China. 421 is the year that Venice is founded at twelve o'clock noon (according to legend) with the dedication of the first church, San Giacomo, at the islet of Rialto (Italy) on March 25th. 422 is the year that the Roman army invade Gaul, they capture and execute the Frankish king Theudemeres with his family. 423 is the year that Emperor Theodosius II refuses Joannes to recognise as emperor and prepares for war on Winter NaNth. 424 is the year that Emperor Theodosius II nominates his cousin Valentinian, age 5, the imperial title nobilissimus Caesar ("most noble") of the Western Roman Empire on October 23rd. 425 is the year that Buddhism begins to spread to Southeast Asia. 426 is the year that Emperor Theodosius II gives orders to destroy the buildings and pagan temples at Olympia (Greece). 427 is the year that Bonifacius, Roman governor (Last of the Romans), revolts in Africa against emperor Valentinian III. 428 is the year that John succeeds Theodotus as patriarch of Antioch, and gives his support to Nestorius. 429 is the year that Genseric seizes lands from the Berbers and destroys church buildings all over Mauretania. 430 is the year that Peter the Iberian founds a Georgian monastery near Bethlehem. 431 is the year that Greek Neoplatonist philosopher Proclus begins studying at the Academy in Athens. 432 is the year that Sebastianus, son-in-law of Bonifacius, becomes supreme commander (magister militum) of the Western Roman army. 433 is the year that Flavius Aetius returns with support of the Huns back to Italy. 434 is the year that Emperor Theodosius II bribes the Huns (after the death of Rugila) to keep the peace in the Eastern Roman Empire. 435 is the year that Ibas is elected bishop of Edessa. 436 is the year that the Buddhist Srimala Sutra is translated into Chinese by Gunabhadra. 437 is the year that Ambrosius Aurelianus, leader of the Romano-British, defeats the Anglo Saxons under king Vortigern in the Battle of Wallop. 438 is the year that Aelia Eudocia, wife of Theodosius II, goes on a pilgrimage to Jeruzalem, bringing back with her holy relics to prove her faith. 439 is the year that Hun and Roman envoys meet at Margum (modern Bosnia and Herzegovina), an important market town on the Sava River on Winter NaNth. 440 is the year that the Huns under Attila reappear in force along the frontier of the Western Roman Empire. 441 is the year that Pulcheria leaves for the seaport Hebdomon (Turkey) and becomes a nun to support Nestorianism in the Holy Land (Palestine). 442 is the year that the Monastery of St. Shenouda the Archimandrite (White Monastery) near Sohag (Egypt) is built. 443 is the year that Gunabhadra, Indian Buddhist monk, is a invited honored guest by emperor Wen of Liu Song (Liu Song Dynasty). 444 is the year that Dioscorus I becomes Patriarch of Alexandria. 445 is the year that Bleda, co-ruler of the Huns, dies in a hunting accident. 446 is the year that a local synod is held by Turibius of Astorga. 447 is the year that the first entry in the Annales Cambriæ refers to this year. 448 is the year that Rechiar succeeds his father Rechila as king of the Suebi in Galicia (Northern Spain). 449 is the year that the Second Council of Ephesus opens, chaired by Dioscorus, patriarch of Alexandria on August 3rd. 450 is the year that Dome of Baptistry of Neon, Ravenna (Italy), is started to be remodeled (approximate date). 451 is the year that Council of Chalcedon, Ecumenical council of the Christian church on October–November 1 8th. 452 is the year that the Huns under Attila invade Northern Italy. 453 is the year that Attila the Hun is found dead in bed after a wedding feast with the Goth princess Ildica. 454 is the year that the Vandals conquer Malta. 455 is the year that Petronius Maximus, former domesticus ("elite bodyguard") of Aetius, becomes with support of the Roman Senate emperor of the Western Roman Empire on March 17th. 456 is the year that Remistus, Roman general (magister militum), is besieged with a Gothic force at Ravenna and later executed in the Palace in Classis, outside the city on September 17th. 457 is the year that Yazdegerd II dies after a 19-year reign. 458 is the year that the Vandals land in Campania, at the mouth of the Lire or the Garigliano River, and devastate the region on Summer NaNth. 459 is the year that Emperor Leo I signs a peace treaty with the Ostrogoths. 460 is the year that the Hepthalites (White Huns) conquer the remnants of the Kushan Empire and enter India. 461 is the year that Libius Severus, Roman senator from Lucania, is declared emperor of the Western Roman Empire on November 19th. 462 is the year that the Daming calendar is introduced in China by mathematician Zu Chongzhi (425–500). 463 is the year that Childeric I, king of the Salian Franks, allies with the Roman general Aegidius against the Visigoths. 464 is the year that Olybrius becomes a consul in Constantinople. 465 is the year that Song Qian Fei Di, then Song Ming Di become ruler of the Song Dynasty in China. 466 is the year that Peter the Fuller is deposed as Patriarch of Antioch; Julian is elected as his successor. 467 is the year that Anthemius becomes Emperor on April 12th. 468 is the year that the Huns again invade Dacia and are once more repelled by Leo. 469 is the year that the Vandals invade Epirus. 470 is the year that Euric, king of the Visigoths, defeats an attempted invasion of Gaul by the Celtic military leader Riothamus. 471 is the year that Acacius becomes Patriarch of Constantinople. 472 is the year that Mount Vesuvius erupts. 473 is the year that Glycerius is named Emperor. 474 is the year that Zeno is crowned as co-emperor on February 9th. 475 is the year that Flavius Orestes forces western emperor Julius Nepos to flee and declares his son, Romulus Augustus, to be emperor on August 28th. 476 is the year that Romulus Augustus, the last traditionally accepted Emperor of the Western Roman Empire, is deposed by Odoacer on September 4th. 477 is the year that Huneric becomes king of Vandals. 478 is the year that the Song Dynasty ends in China. 479 is the year that the Song Dynasty ends and the Southern Qi Dynasty begins in southern China. 480 is the year that Narasimhagupta Baladitya succeeds his father Skandagupta as ruler of the Gupta Empire. 481 is the year that Baekje, Silla, and Daegaya form an alliance against Goguryeo. 482 is the year that Qi Gao Di becomes ruler of the Chinese Southern Qi Dynasty. 483 is the year that General Illus and Verina attempt to overthrow Emperor Zeno and place a general named Leontius on the throne. 484 is the year that Gundobad proclaims the Burgundian Code. 485 is the year that Aelle of Sussex fights the Brythons at the stream of Mearcread. 486 is the year that the Battle of Mercredesburne is fought between Aelle's army and the Britons. 487 is the year that the Earth probably went around the Sun. 488 is the year that Kavadh I succeeds Balash in Persia. 489 is the year that the first Confucian Temple is constructed in north China (outside the ancestral temple at Qufu). 490 is the year that the majority of Odoacer's army, including his magister militum Tufa, surrenders to Theodoric the Great in Milan on April 1st. 491 is the year that Anastasius I becomes emperor on April 11th. 492 is the year that Pope Gelasius I succeeds Pope Felix III as the 49th pope on March 1st. 493 is the year that the Frankish king Clovis I marries the Burgundian princess Clotilde. 494 is the year that Pope Gelasius I delineates the relationship between church and state. 495 is the year that Cerdic of Wessex raids Hampshire. 496 is the year that Pope Anastasius II succeeds Pope Gelasius I as the 50th pope on November 24th. 497 is the year that the Shaolin Temple is founded (according to the Jiaqing Chongxiu Yitongzhi). 498 is the year that Emperor Anastasius I reforms the monetary system, using Greek numerals instead of Roman. 499 is the year that Kavadh I of Persia deposes his brother Djamasp and restores himself as king of Persia.

500 is the year that the Frankish Kingdom is formed. 501 is the year that Ahkal Mo' Naab' I comes to power in the Maya city of Palenque. 502 is the year that the Southern Qi Dynasty ends and the Liang Dynasty begins in southern China. 503 is the year that we do not know what happened. 504 is the year that Theodoric the Great defeats the Gepids as the Ostrogoths sack Belgrade. 505 is the year that the Earth probably went around the Sun. 506 is the year that the city of Dara in Mesopotamia is fortified by emperor Anastasius I as a frontier against Persia. 507 is the year that the first and smaller of the two Buddhas of Bamyan is erected in central Afghanistan. 508 is the year that Clovis I establishes Paris (Lutetia) as his capital. 509 is the year that we do not know what happened. 510 is the year that nothing remarkable happened. 511 is the year that Macedonius II is deposed as Patriarch of Constantinople, and replaced by Timothy I. 512 is the year that Emperor Anastasius I ends a period of moderate eclectic policy, and starts strongly favoring his own monophysitist beliefs. 513 is the year that Vigorus becomes bishop of Bayeux. 514 is the year that Pope Hormisdas succeeds Pope Symmachus as the 52nd pope on July 20th. 515 is the year that the Revolt of Vitalian is subdued by forces loyal to Byzantine emperor Anastasius I. 516 is the year that Sigismund, son of Gundobad, becomes king of Burgundy. 517 is the year that Sigismund of Burgundy is opposed by his son; he later has his son strangled. 518 is the year that Justin becomes Byzantine emperor on July 9th. 519 is the year that Jacob of Serugh becomes bishop of Batnan. 520 is the year that the kingdom of East Anglia is formed (approximate date). 521 is the year that Boëthius introduces Greek musical letter notation to the West. 522 is the year that Amalaric becomes king of the Visigoths. 523 is the year that Leptis Magna is sacked by Berber raiders. 524 is the year that Ahkal Mo' Naab' I, ruler of the Maya city of Palenque, dies on December 1st. 525 is the year that the Arian Baptistery of S. Maria is built in Cosmedin, Ravenna. 526 is the year that an earthquake kills approximately 250,000 in Syria and Antioch on Probably between May and May 29 NaNth. 527 is the year that the Church of the Nativity, Bethlehem, is rebuilt until 565. 528 is the year that Xiao Zhuang Di succeeds Xiao Ming Di as ruler of the Chinese Northern Wei Dynasty. 529 is the year that the Samaritans revolt and are defeated; the Church of the Nativity is burnt down during the revolt. 530 is the year that St. Brendan climbs to the top of Mount Brandon, to look for The Americas. 531 is the year that Khosrau I succeeds Kavadh I as king of Persia. 532 is the year that the Franks invade the kingdom of Burgundy. 533 is the year that Theodebert I becomes king of Austrasia. 534 is the year that Gelimer surrenders to Byzantine general Belisarius, after spending a miserable winter in the mountains of Numidia. 535 is the year that Pope Agapetus I succeeds Pope John II as the 57th pope on May 13th. 536 is the year that Pope Silverius succeeds Pope Agapetus I on June or June 8 1st. 537 is the year that Pope Vigilius succeeds Pope Silverius as the 59th pope, when the latter is deposed by Belisarius at the order of Justinian on March 29th. 538 is the year that the Kofun era ends and the Asuka period, the second part of the Yamato period in Japan, begins. 539 is the year that Antioch is struck by an earthquake on November 29th. 540 is the year that Benedict of Nursia writes his monastic Rule. 541 is the year that Anicius Faustus Albinus Basilius is appointed as consul in Constantinople, the last person to hold this office on January 1st. 542 is the year that Ostrogoth king Totila reconquers Naples, Benevento, and other parts of Italy. 543 is the year that the doctrine of apocatastasis is condemned by the Synod of Constantinople. 544 is the year that Battle of Cillium in Africa, and death of Solomon. 545 is the year that the monastery of Clonmacnoise is built on the River Shannon. 546 is the year that the Byzantines ally with the Lombards against the Gepids. 547 is the year that Emperor Justinian and His Attendants, mosaic on north wall of the apse, Basilica of San Vitale, Ravenna, Italy, is made (approximate date). 548 is the year that Battle of the Fields of Cato - Byzantines under John Troglita crush Moorish revolt. 549 is the year that Agila succeeds Theudigisel as king of the Visigoths. 550 is the year that Gupta Empire falls (approximate date). 551 is the year that the Byzantine Empire captures part of southern Spain from the Visigoths. 552 is the year that Eutychius becomes Patriarch of Constantinople. 553 is the year that the Fifth Ecumenical Council is held. 554 is the year that Gong Di succeeds Fei Di as ruler of the Chinese Western Wei Dynasty. 555 is the year that Taliesin becomes court bard to King Brochfael of Powys (approximate date). 556 is the year that Cynric and Ceawlin of Wessex fight against the Britons at Beranburh. 557 is the year that the Liang Dynasty ends and the Chen Dynasty begins in southern China; its first ruler is Chen Wu Di. 558 is the year that Clotaire I reunites the Frankish kingdom. 559 is the year that the Kutrigurs and Huns under Zabergan invade and raid Byzantine territory, but are driven back near Constantinople by Belisarius. 560 is the year that Custennin ap Cado abdicates as King of Dumnonia, and retires to a monastery where he is eventually murdered. 561 is the year that Jnanagupta begins translating Buddhist texts into Chinese. 562 is the year that Sigebert I repels an attack on Austrasia by the Avars. 563 is the year that Saint Columba, the Irish missionary, founds his mission to the Picts and his monastery on Iona. 564 is the year that nothing interesting came to pass. 565 is the year that the Uyghurs are conquered by the Göktürks. 566 is the year that the Earth probably went around the Sun. 567 is the year that the Gepids are conquered by the Avars. 568 is the year that a Turkish khan sends emissaries to Byzantium. 569 is the year that the King of the Garamantes signs a peace treaty with Byzantium. 570 is the year that First mention of the Spear of Destiny (approximate date). 571 is the year that the Monophysites again reject the Council of Chalcedon, causing another schism. 572 is the year that Theodric succeeds his brother Æthelric as king of Bernicia (traditional date). 573 is the year that the Battle of Arfderydd is fought between Gwenddoleu ap Ceidio and the sons of Eliffer, Gwrgi and Peredur. 574 is the year that Emperor Justin II retires, choosing Tiberius II Constantine as his heir. 575 is the year that Pope Benedict I succeeds Pope John III as the 62nd pope on June 2nd. 576 is the year that the Visigoths establish the capital of their kingdom in Toledo (present-day Spain). 577 is the year that Eutychius is restored as Patriarch of Constantinople. 578 is the year that Tiberius II Constantine succeeds Justin II as Byzantine Emperor on October 5th. 579 is the year that Hormizd IV succeeds Khosrau I as king of Persia. 580 is the year that Ethelbert becomes king of Kent. 581 is the year that the Sui Dynasty replaces the Northern Zhou Dynasty, the last of the Northern Dynasties in China. 582 is the year that John Nesteutes becomes Patriarch of Constantinople. 583 is the year that Eborico (also called Eurico) succeeds his father Miro as King of the Suevi. 584 is the year that Kubrat becomes king of the Bulgars (approximate date). 585 is the year that Emperor Yōmei ascends to the throne of Japan. 586 is the year that Constantine of Kernyw converts to Christianity. 587 is the year that Emperor Sushun ascends to the throne of Ancient Japan. 588 is the year that the Skellig Michael monastery is founded on a steep rocky island off the coast of Ireland. 589 is the year that the Chinese scholar-official Yan Zhitui makes the first reference to the use of toilet paper in human history. 590 is the year that Kadungon succeeds Avani Culamani as ruler of the Pandyan kingdom in India. 591 is the year that a Mesoamerican ballgame court is dedicated at the Mayan city of Chinkultic on May 21st. 592 is the year that the Persian usurper Bahram Chobin is defeated by Khosrau II at the Battle of Blarathon. 593 is the year that Altar to Amitabha Buddha is made. 594 is the year that Byzantine Emperor Maurice disposes of Priscos and installs his own brother Peter as commander-in-chief in charge of the war against the Avars. 595 is the year that the Lombards sack Terracina in Italy. 596 is the year that Pope Gregory I sends Augustine of Canterbury to convert the Anglo-Saxons to Christianity. 597 is the year that Pope Gregory I sends a delegation of monks under the Roman Augustine to England to convert the English. 598 is the year that we do not know what happened. 599 is the year that Raedwald becomes king of East Anglia (approximate date).

600 is the year that the moldboard plow is invented in eastern Europe. 601 is the year that Peter (Byzantine general) defeats the Eurasian Avars. 602 is the year that a series of wars begin between the Byzantine Empire and the Sassanid Empire. 603 is the year that the future Pope Boniface III is appointed papal legate to Constantinople. 604 is the year that Justus founds a cathedral in Rochester, England. 605 is the year that the Chinese Zhaozhou Bridge is completed under the Sui Dynasty, the earliest known fully stone open-spandrel segmental arch bridge in the world. 606 is the year that the diocese of Aquileia becomes a patriarchate. 607 is the year that the Pantheon in Rome is converted into a church. 608 is the year that the observance of Halloween in the Roman Catholic Church is first recorded. 609 is the year that Shibi Khan becomes the khagan in the Eastern Turkish Empire. 610 is the year that Gundemar succeeds Witteric as king of the Visigoths. 611 is the year that the Earth probably went around the Sun. 612 is the year that Theuderic II becomes king of Austrasia. 613 is the year that Muhammad begins preaching Islam in public. 614 is the year that the Palace of Diocletian is damaged by the Avars, who sack nearby Salona. 615 is the year that Edwin of Northumbria takes refuge in East Anglia; he marries Cwenburga, daughter of Cearl of Mercia. 616 is the year that Eadbald succeeds Ethelbert as king of Kent. 617 is the year that the Persian Army, under the command of General Spahbodh Shaahin, conquers Chalcedon after a long siege. 618 is the year that a civil war begins in Medina. 619 is the year that the Second Perso-Turkic War is fought and ended with Decisive Sassanid victory. 620 is the year that Medina is converted to Islam. 621 is the year that Wang Shichong surrenders to Li Shimin following Dou Jiande's defeat on June 4th. 622 is the year that Wang Shichong surrenders to Li Shimin following Dou Jiande's defeat on June 4th. 623 is the year that Clotaire II, king of the Franks, makes his son Dagobert I king of Austrasia. 624 is the year that the Battle of Badr is fought on March 17th. 625 is the year that Battle of Uhud (Muhammad retreats against the inhabitants of Mecca), which they consider a victory on March 23rd. 626 is the year that Emperor Gaozu of Tang China abdicates in favor of his son Li Shimin on September 3rd. 627 is the year that Paulinus, a Roman missionary, baptizes King Edwin of Deira on April 11th. 628 is the year that Brahmagupta writes the Brahmasphutasiddhanta, an early, yet very advanced, math book. 629 is the year that the Battle of Mu'tah, the first Muslim expedition outside Arabia, fails to take the lands east of the Jordan River. 630 is the year that the Byzantine-Arab Wars begin. 631 is the year that the Battle of Wogastisburg is fought between the Slavs led by Samo, and the Franks led by their king, Dagobert I. 632 is the year that the Last Sermon (Khutbah, Khutbatul Wada') of Prophet Muhammad on February 23rd. 633 is the year that Arab armies invade Syria and Iraq. 634 is the year that Umar ibn al-Khattab succeeds Abu Bakr as Sunni Caliph. 635 is the year that the Chinese historian Yao Silian completes the Book of Liang. 636 is the year that the historical texts of the Book of Northern Qi, Book of Chen, and Book of Sui are compiled in China during the Tang Dynasty. 637 is the year that Muslim forces under the Rashidun Caliphate conquer Jerusalem, Aleppo and Antioch. 638 is the year that the Islamic calendar is introduced. 639 is the year that the Plague of Emmaus breaks out. 640 is the year that Pope John IV succeeds Pope Severinus as the 72nd pope on December 24th. 641 is the year that Byzantine Emperor Heraclius dies on February 11th. 642 is the year that the earliest surviving dated Arabic papyrus, PERF 558, and the earliest known Arabic text with diacritical marks is written. 643 is the year that Pirooz, the son of the last Sassanid king of Persia, flees to Tang Dynasty China. 644 is the year that the Tang dynasty of China begins the invasion of Goguryo. 645 is the year that Goguryeo general Yang Man-chun resists the Emperor Taizong of Tang. 646 is the year that an edict of the Taika Reforms is promulgated in Japan. 647 is the year that the first Muslim invasion of North Africa led by Uthman ibn Affan of the Rashidun Caliphate. 648 is the year that the Book of Jin is compiled in China during the Tang Dynasty. 649 is the year that Reccaswinth succeeds his father Chindaswinth as king of the Visigoths. 650 is the year that Hungry Tigress Jataka, panel of the Tamamushi Shrine, Horyu-ji, is made. 651 is the year that the Qur'an is written down. 652 is the year that a new palace of Japan is moved to Naniwa. 653 is the year that Sigeberht II the Good succeeds Sigeberht I the Little as king of Essex. 654 is the year that Rhodes is invaded by an Arab force; remains of the Colossus of Rhodes are sold off. 655 is the year that Clovis II is succeeded by Clotaire III as king of the Franks. 656 is the year that Ali succeeds Uthman as Caliph. 657 is the year that Saint Hilda founds an abbey on the Yorkshire coast at Whitby. 658 is the year that Tang China defeats Western Turkic Kaganate. 659 is the year that we do not know what happened. 660 is the year that Emperor Gaozong of Tang suffers a stroke; his wife Wu Zetian starts to rule. 661 is the year that Emperor Tenji ascends to the throne of Japan after Empress Saimei's death. 662 is the year that the regent Grimuald usurps the kingship of the Lombards, driving Perctarit into exile and killing Godepert. 663 is the year that a brief outbreak of plague hits Britain. 664 is the year that the Synod of Whitby is held in Northumbria on September NaNth. 665 is the year that the city of Seongnam is renamed Hansanju. 666 is the year that Chertsey Abbey is founded. 667 is the year that the city of Oderzo is destroyed by the Lombards. 668 is the year that the Emperor of Japan hunts on the Moor of Ōmi-Gamōno. 669 is the year that we do not know what happened. 670 is the year that Hōryū-ji, the Buddhist temple in Japan, burns down; its reconstruction is immediately begun. 671 is the year that a clepsydra is placed in the capital of Japan on June 10th. 672 is the year that Wamba succeeds Reccaswinth as king of the Visigoths. 673 is the year that Emperor Temmu assumes the Chrysanthemum throne of Japan at the Palace of Kiyomihara in Asuka on March 20th. 674 is the year that the first glass windows are placed in English churches. 675 is the year that the abbeys of Abingdon, England and Bath are founded. 676 is the year that Pope Donus succeeds Pope Adeodatus as the 78th pope on November 2nd. 677 is the year that nothing remarkable happened. 678 is the year that Pope Agatho succeeds Pope Donus as the 79th pope on June 27th. 679 is the year that Adamnan becomes abbot of the monastery on Iona. 680 is the year that the Bulgars subjugate the country of current-day Bulgaria. 681 is the year that Wilfrid of York is expelled from Northumbria by Ecgfrith, and retires into Sussex. 682 is the year that Pope Leo II succeeds Pope Agatho as the 80th pope on August 17th. 683 is the year that the reign of Pacal the Great, ruler of Maya state of Palenque, comes to an end. 684 is the year that Pope Benedict II succeeds Pope Leo II as the 81st pope on June 26th. 685 is the year that Pope John V succeeds Pope Benedict II as the 82nd pope on July 23rd. 686 is the year that Caedwalla exterminates the Jutes of the Isle of Wight and kills King Arwald. 687 is the year that Egica succeeds Erwig as king of the Visigoths. 688 is the year that Emperor Justinian II of the Byzantine Empire defeats the Bulgarians. 689 is the year that we do not know what happened. 690 is the year that the approximate date of the earliest known blindfold chess, played by Sa'id bin Jubair. 691 is the year that Theuderic III is succeeded by Clovis IV as king of Austrasia. 692 is the year that the Quinisext Council, held in Constantinople, lays the foundation for Orthodox Canon Law. 693 is the year that nothing remarkable happened. 694 is the year that Ine of Wessex makes peace with Kent. 695 is the year that Childebert III succeeds Clovis IV as king of the Franks. 696 is the year that the Earth probably went around the Sun. 697 is the year that Emperor Mommu succeeds Empress Jitō on the throne of Japan. 698 is the year that the Byzantine general Heraclius, brother of Tiberius III, launches a campaign into Syria, defeats an army from Antioch and raids as far as Samosata on Autumn–winter NaNth. 699 is the year that Umayyad troops invade Armenia and secure submission of Smbat VI Bagratuni.

700 is the year that Musa bin Nusair defeats the Berber army in Algeria, ending resistance against the Arabs there. 701 is the year that Wittiza succeeds his grandfather Ergica as king of the Visigoths. 702 is the year that the Umayyad Mosque at Damascus is completed. 703 is the year that Elias I becomes Catholicos of Armenia. 704 is the year that the Earth probably went around the Sun. 705 is the year that Pope John VII succeeds Pope John VI (died on 11 January) as the 86th Pope on March 1st. 706 is the year that Umayyad Caliph al-Walid I begins the Great Mosque of Damascus. 707 is the year that a large Umayyad army under Maslamah ibn Abd al-Malik invades Asia Minor and lays siege to Tyana. 708 is the year that the Japanese court is moved from Heian to Nara. 709 is the year that a storm separates the Channel Islands of Jethou and Herm. 710 is the year that a Muslim army is invited into Ceuta by its governor, Count Julian, who, being an opponent of Roderick, encourages them to invade the Iberian peninsula. 711 is the year that Childebert III died and is succeeded by Dagobert III as king of Austrasia. 712 is the year that the Kojiki, a history of Japan, is completed. 713 is the year that Emperor Xuanzong of Tang starts to rule in Ancient China. 714 is the year that an earthquake strikes Syria on February 28th. 715 is the year that Saint Boniface sets out on a missionary expedition to the Frisians. 716 is the year that the Ummayads conquer Lisbon. 717 is the year that Umayyad caliph al-Walid I ibn Abd al-Malik is succeeded by Sulayman ibn Abd al-Malik. 718 is the year that the world's oldest hotel, Hoshi Ryokan, is founded in Ishikawa Prefecture, Japan. 719 is the year that the West Saxon monk Winifrid is sent by Pope Gregory II, who gives him the name Boniface, to evangelize in Germany and reorganize the church there. 720 is the year that the Byzantine emperor Leo III the Isaurian orders the execution of the ex-emperor Anastasius II. 721 is the year that Prague is founded (according to legend) by the Princess Libuše and her husband Přemysl, founder of the dynasty with the same name. 722 is the year that a combined Viking and Cornish army defeat an army of Wessex at the Battle of Hehil. 723 is the year that the world's first mechanical clock is allegedly built in China (See celestial globe). 724 is the year that Emperor Shōmu succeeds Empress Genshō on the throne of Japan. 725 is the year that Bede writes On the reckoning of time (De temporum ratione) explaining how to calculate medieval Easter. 726 is the year that the first annual Sumo tournament in Japan is held by Emperor Seibu. 727 is the year that Pope Gregory II condemns iconoclasm, causing Byzantine Italy to break with the Empire. 728 is the year that Liutprand, King of the Lombards occupies all of the exarchate. 729 is the year that the Earth probably went around the Sun. 730 is the year that Umayyad troops sack the Byzantine fortress of Charsianon on September/October NaNth. 731 is the year that Bede completes his Historia ecclesiastica gentis Anglorum. 732 is the year that Venus occults Jupiter on June 26th. 733 is the year that nothing remarkable happened. 734 is the year that the Franks defeat the Frisians in the Battle of the Boarn. 735 is the year that Khöshöö Tsaidam Monuments of Bilge Khan of Turkish Khanate his brother Kül Tigin. 736 is the year that the Earth probably went around the Sun. 737 is the year that Favila becomes king of Asturias after Pelayo's death. 738 is the year that Saint Boniface visits Rome, and goes on to establish bishoprics in Bavaria. 739 is the year that Thawra revolt in Tanger against the Umayyad rulers. 740 is the year that Battle of Akroinon in Anatolia, a significant Byzantine victory over the Umayyads, halts the impetus of Arab attacks into Anatolia. 741 is the year that a nunnery given by the Alamannic noblewoman Beata on Lützelau island is first mentioned. 742 is the year that Saint Sturm establishes the abbey of Fulda (or 744?. 743 is the year that Constantine V re-ascends the throne of the Byzantine Empire. 744 is the year that Ratchis succeeds Hildeprand as king of the Lombards on October NaNth. 745 is the year that Bubonic plague in Constantinople subsequently sweeps through Europe. 746 is the year that Guru Rinpoche, an Indian saint, traveled to Bhutan to cure the king of Bumthang. 747 is the year that the Shin-Yakushi-ji Buddhist temple is founded. 748 is the year that the city of Baalbek is sacked. 749 is the year that Abbasid forces under Qahtaba ibn Shabib al-Ta'i defeat a large Ummayad army at Isfahan and move into Iraq, taking Kufa in September. 750 is the year that the Western Paradise of Amitabha Buddha, detail of a wall painting in Cave 217, Dunhuang, Gansu, is made. 751 is the year that Pepin the Short is elected as king of the Franks by the Frankish nobility, marking the end of the Merovingian and beginning of the Carolingian dynasty. 752 is the year that Cuthred of Wessex leads a successful rebellion against Aethelbald of Mercia at Battle Edge, Burford. 753 is the year that Samarkand is conquered by Arabs. 754 is the year that the oldest document mentioning the city of Ferrara is from this year (approximate date). 755 is the year that an Lushan begins the Anshi Rebellion against the Tang Dynasty state of China on December 16th. 756 is the year that Desiderius succeeds Aistulf as king of the Lombards. 757 is the year that Tassilo III, duke of the Bavarians, recognizes the supremacy of Frankish king Pepin the Short. 758 is the year that the moderate Ibadites under the Persian 'Abd al-Rahman Iban Rustam conquer Kairouan and massacre the Sofrites Kharijites. 759 is the year that Exceptional winter in England. 760 is the year that the Kailash Temple is built on the orders of Krishna I of the Rashtrakutas. 761 is the year that the city of Oviedo is founded by Máximo and Fromestano. 762 is the year that Abbasid caliph al-Mansur founds a new capital at Baghdad, Iraq on July 30th. 763 is the year that Ciniod succeeds Bridei V as king of the Picts. 764 is the year that Mauricius Galba becomes Doge of Venice. 765 is the year that Papal privileges are restored in Beneventino and Tuscany (and partly in Spoleto). 766 is the year that Nicetas is appointed Patriarch of Constantinople on November 16th. 767 is the year that the Kharijite Berbers of Tlemcen and Tiaret try to conquer Ifriqiya (Tunisia) from the Abbasid caliphate but fail to conquer the capital, Kairouan. 768 is the year that Pope Stephen III succeeds Pope Paul I as the 94th pope on August 7th. 769 is the year that Pope Stephen III holds a council; papal election procedure is changed and the devotion to icons is confirmed. 770 is the year that Emperor Kōnin ascends to the throne of Japan, succeeding Empress Shōtoku. 771 is the year that Carloman I, King of the Franks, dies, leaving his brother Charlemagne king of the now complete Frankish kingdom on December 4th. 772 is the year that Pope Adrian I (also referred to as Hadrian) succeeds Pope Stephen III as the 95th pope on February 9th. 773 is the year that the concept of the number zero is introduced to the city of Baghdad. 774 is the year that Silo succeeds Aurelio as king of Asturias. 775 is the year that Alpin II succeeds Ciniod I as king of the Picts. 776 is the year that the Battle of Otford is fought between Mercia and Kent. 777 is the year that Ibn Rustam is recognized imam of the Ibadis in Maghrib. 778 is the year that Widukind returns to Saxony from Denmark. 779 is the year that Offa's Dyke is constructed. 780 is the year that the city of Osnabrück is founded by Charlemagne (approximate date). 781 is the year that Alcuin becomes Charlemagne's chief adviser on religious and educational matters. 782 is the year that Charlemagne summons the monk and scholar Alcuin of York to head the palace school at Aachen in order to inspire the revival of education in Europe. 783 is the year that we do not know what happened. 784 is the year that Paul IV abdicates as Patriarch of Constantinople on August 31st. 785 is the year that the Frankish empire conquers Girona from the Moors. 786 is the year that a council is organized in Constantinople, but is disturbed by soldiers. 787 is the year that Conall succeeds Drest as king of the Picts. 788 is the year that Bermudo I succeeds Mauregato as king of Asturias. 789 is the year that Eadburh marries Beorhtric of Wessex. 790 is the year that Angilbert is made abbot of Saint-Riquier. 791 is the year that Alfonso II becomes king of Asturias. 792 is the year that the Westphalians rise up against the Saxons (see Charlemagne). 793 is the year that a jihad under Hisham I takes place. 794 is the year that Kyoto becomes the Japanese capital, ending the Nara period, and beginning the Heian period. 795 is the year that City of Paderborn founded by Charlemagne in Westphalia. 796 is the year that Coenwulf becomes king of Mercia on December NaNth. 797 is the year that Irene of Athens's orders are carried out; her son is blinded, and she is declared empress the next day on August 15th. 798 is the year that Bahlul Ibn Marzuq revolted in Zaragoza against the central government of Muslim Al-Andalus. 799 is the year that Pope Leo III, aided by Charles the Great, returns to Rome on 29 November 29th.

800 is the year that Itza culture starts in Mesoamerica (approximate date). 801 is the year that Louis the Pious occupies Barcelona on December 28th. 802 is the year that Egbert becomes king of Wessex. 803 is the year that Venice is recognized as independent by the Byzantine Empire. 804 is the year that the Inscription of Sukabumi from Eastern Java marks the beginning of the Javanese language on March 25th. 805 is the year that Tang Shunzong succeeds Tang Dezong as emperor of China, but does not last till the end of the year. 806 is the year that Nicephorus is elected patriarch of Constantinople, succeeding Tarasius on April 12th. 807 is the year that Li Ji Pu becomes Prime Minister to Emperor Xian Zong in China. 808 is the year that the Abbasid capital is moved north from Baghdad to Samarra. 809 is the year that the Bulgars capture Sofia. 810 is the year that China demands the return of territory by Tibet. 811 is the year that Michael I Rangabe is declared Byzantine emperor; Stauracius retires to a monastery on October 1st. 812 is the year that the second Battle of Roncevaux Pass is fought between the Basques and the Franks. 813 is the year that Louis the Pious is crowned co-emperor of the Franks with his father Charlemagne. 814 is the year that Conflict erupts between Emperor Leo V and Patriarch Nicephorus on the subject of iconoclasm; Leo deposes Nicephorus, Nicephorus excommunicates Leo. 815 is the year that Egbert of Wessex ravages the territories of the west Welsh (Cornwall). 816 is the year that Pope Stephen IV (sometimes referred to as Stephen V) succeeds Pope Leo III as the 97th pope on June 22nd. 817 is the year that Louis the Pious divides his empire among his sons; Louis the German becomes king of East Francia, Lothar I becomes co-emperor. 818 is the year that Bishop Theodulf of Orléans is deposed and imprisoned, after becoming involved in a conspiracy of King Bernard of Italy against Louis the Pious. 819 is the year that Nominoe becomes earl of Vannes, Brittany. 820 is the year that Fedelmid mac Crimthainn assumes the kingship of Munster. 821 is the year that Tang Mu Zong becomes emperor of China. 822 is the year that the civil war between Byzantine Emperor Michael II and the general Thomas the Slav continues. 823 is the year that Defeat of the Byzantine rebel Thomas the Slav by the forces of Michael II at Diabasis in Thrace. 824 is the year that the Constitutio Romana establishes the authority of the Holy Roman Emperors over the pope. 825 is the year that Egbert of Wessex defeats Beornwulf of Mercia at Ellandun. 826 is the year that the Danish king Harald Klak accepts Christianity on June 24th. 827 is the year that Agnellus Iustinianus Particiacus appointed Roman consul and duke of Venice. 828 is the year that a Coptic revolt breaks out in Egypt. 829 is the year that the synod of Mainz is held. 830 is the year that Earliest date of composition for the Historia Brittonum, attributed to Nennius, and known for its list of 12 battles of King Arthur. 831 is the year that Saint Ansgar founds the first church in Sweden, at Birka. 832 is the year that Pepin I of Aquitaine and Louis the German revolt against Louis the Pious, Emperor of the Franks. 833 is the year that Mojmír I unifies Great Moravia. 834 is the year that Jona River in Switzerland was first mentioned. 835 is the year that Ragnar Lodbrok rises to power (approximate date). 836 is the year that the construction of Mosque of Uqba, Kairouan, Tunisia, begins. 837 is the year that Pietro Tradonico is elected Doge of Venice. 838 is the year that Discovery of a conspiracy to assassinate Caliph Mu'tasim and place his nephew Al-Abbas ibn al-Ma'mun on the throne. 839 is the year that the Saracen troops established in the South pillage Ancona in Central Italy. 840 is the year that Tang Wu Zong succeeds Tang Wen Zong as emperor of China. 841 is the year that the Norse town of Dyflinn or Dublin is founded in Ireland. 842 is the year that Uurad is succeeded by Bred, then Ciniod as King of the Picts. 843 is the year that Kenneth I (Cináed mac Ailpín), King of the Scots, also becomes King of the Picts, thus becoming the first monarch of the new nation of Scotland. 844 is the year that Rhodri Mawr ('the Great') becomes king of Gwynedd. 845 is the year that the Vikings also sack Hamburg and Melun. 846 is the year that the Moors recapture León. 847 is the year that Bari is captured by the Saracens. 848 is the year that Chola Dynasty starts to rule (approximate date). 849 is the year that nothing remarkable happened. 850 is the year that Guntherus becomes Bishop of Cologne on April 20th. 851 is the year that Oldest known mention of the Andaman Islands. 852 is the year that Boris I Michael succeeds the duumvirate of Malamir and Presian as monarch of Bulgaria. 853 is the year that Tuan Ch'eng-Shih publishes Miscellaneous Offerings from Yu-yang in China. 854 is the year that Horik II succeeds Horik I as king of Denmark. 855 is the year that Anastasius is made anti-pope by Lothair. 856 is the year that Ethelbald usurps the throne of Wessex from his father Ethelwulf. 857 is the year that the Vikings raid Dorestad. 858 is the year that Emperor Seiwa ascends the throne of Japan. 859 is the year that the University of Al Karaouine is founded in Fes, Morocco (recognized by the Guinness Book of World Records as the oldest university in the world). 860 is the year that Ethelbert succeeds as king of Wessex. 861 is the year that Michael III and Bardas invade Bulgaria. 862 is the year that Fan Chuo finishes his Manchu (Book of the Southern Tribes). 863 is the year that Carloman revolts against his father Louis the German a second time. 864 is the year that Louis II marches against Rome but, getting ill, decides to make peace with the Pope. 865 is the year that Ethelred succeeds as king of Wessex (or 866). 866 is the year that Pope Nicholas I forbids the use of torture in prosecutions for witchcraft. 867 is the year that Patriarch Photius I of Constantinople is removed from office and banished; Ignatius is patriarch of Constantinople once again on September NaNth. 868 is the year that Ratramnus writes Contra Graecorum Opposita. 869 is the year that Western Emperor Louis II allies with eastern Emperor Basil I against the Saracens. 870 is the year that Michael II succeeds Michael I as Patriarch of Alexandria. 871 is the year that Louis II captures Bari, the headquarters of the Saracens. 872 is the year that Gascony becomes an independent kingdom, with Sancho I Mitarra as its first king. 873 is the year that the Vikings raid Dorestad. 874 is the year that the territory of the Vistulans is conquered by King Svatopluk I of Great Moravia. 875 is the year that Harald Fairhair subdues the rovers on Orkney and Shetland and adds them to his kingdom. 876 is the year that nothing interesting came to pass. 877 is the year that the Danes take Exeter, England. 878 is the year that Rhodri, the first King of Wales to be known as "the Great", is killed in battle. 879 is the year that Louis the Stammerer, king of West Francia dies, and is succeeded by his sons Louis III and Carloman II. 880 is the year that a bishopric is established in Nitra. 881 is the year that St. Cäcilien, Cäcilienstraße, Cologne is founded as a college for women. 882 is the year that Oleg of Novgorod takes Kiev and makes it his capital. 883 is the year that the Balaton Principality is conquered by King Svatopluk I of Great Moravia. 884 is the year that Charles the Fat becomes King of Western Francia, thus for the last time reuniting the Frankish kingdom on December 12th. 885 is the year that Oldest known mention of Baky, Azerbaijan. 886 is the year that Charles II of France purchases peace with Vikings and Rollo of Normandy, then lifts his siege of Paris. 887 is the year that Odo, Count of Paris ascends to the throne of Western Francia (modern France). 888 is the year that Shaftesbury Abbey is founded in Dorset, England. 889 is the year that Donald II succeeds Eochaid I as king of Scotland. 890 is the year that the Welsh king Anarawd, King of Gwynedd, makes the first ceremonial visit to an English court (that of Alfred the Great). 891 is the year that Pope Formosus succeeds Pope Stephen V as the 111th pope on October 6th. 892 is the year that Arnulf of Carinthia and his Magyar (Hungarian) allies invade Great Moravia. 893 is the year that Galindo II Aznárez succeeds Aznar II Galíndez as Count of Aragon. 894 is the year that a Byzantine-Hungarian alliance forces Bulgar invaders to agree to a peace settlement. 895 is the year that Approximate date of composition of the Musica enchiriadis, the beginnings of western polyphonic music. 896 is the year that the Bulgarians, under Simeon I, defeat the Byzantine Empire at Bulgarophygon. 897 is the year that the Cadaver Synod is held on January NaNth. 898 is the year that Magyar tribes found the state of Szekesfehervar in Hungary. 899 is the year that Regino of Prüm is expelled from Prüm and becomes abbot of St. Martin's in Trier.

900 is the year that Pueblo Bonito, Chaco Canyon, New Mexico, is built on C. 900 –1230 NaNth. 901 is the year that Speech of Arethas of Caesarea at the occasion of the Epiphany on January 6th. 902 is
