year that Emperor Juntoku is briefly succeeded by Emperor Chūkyō on the throne of Japan on May 13th. 1222 is the year that Royal Standard of Scotland adopted. 1223 is the year that the Franciscan Rule is approved by Pope Honorius III. 1224 is the year that the last Muslims inhabitants are expelled from Sicily and Malta. 1225 is the year that the Magna Carta is reissued for the third time. 1226 is the year that the king Sancho II of Portugal launches a large offensive against the Muslims and takes the city of Elvas. 1227 is the year that Pope Gregory IX succeeds Pope Honorius III as the 178th pope on March 19th. 1228 is the year that Conrad IV of Germany becomes titular King of Jerusalem, with Frederick II, Holy Roman Emperor as regent on April 25th. 1229 is the year that the Treaty of Paris brings the Albigensian Crusade to an end on April 12th. 1230 is the year that the Kingdoms of León and Galicia unite with the Kingdoms of Castile and Toledo under Ferdinand III on September 24th. 1231 is the year that Ardengus becomes bishop of Florence. 1232 is the year that the Almohad army besieges Ceuta where Abu Musa, the rebellious brother of the caliph, has received shelter and the support of the population. 1233 is the year that the Inquisition is established. 1234 is the year that the Manden region raises against the Kaniaga kingdom. 1235 is the year that the Lancaster Royal Grammar School is founded. 1236 is the year that a tournament at Tickhill in England turns into a battle between northerners and southerners, but peace is restored by the papal legate. 1237 is the year that the Livonian Brothers of the Sword unite with the Teutonic Knights. 1238 is the year that Founder of the Nasrid dynasty, Mohammed I ibn Nasr, begins Alhambra complex on the site of a pre-Islamic fortress. 1239 is the year that Frederick II, Holy Roman Emperor conducts the Siege of Faenza. 1240 is the year that Tuan Mash'ika, an Arab, travels and introduces Islam to Sulu. 1241 is the year that Emperor Lizong of Song China accepts the Neo-Confucian teachings of the late Zhu Xi, including his commentary on the Four Books. 1242 is the year that the archbishop of Wiesbaden conquers the city from the Duke of Nassau. 1243 is the year that the city of Brno is founded in what is now Czech Republic. 1244 is the year that James I of Aragon takes the Muslim-held city of Janita after several months of siege on May 22nd. 1245 is the year that a rebellion occurs against King Sancho II of Portugal in favour of his brother Afonso. 1246 is the year that the Gothic chapel of Sainte-Chapelle is built. 1247 is the year that Nijmegen becomes part of Gelderland. 1248 is the year that Roger Bacon publishes the formula for black powder in Europe. 1249 is the year that the Battle of Fossalta is fought between the Holy Roman Empire and the Lombard League on May 26th. 1250 is the year that the Parlement law courts of ancien régime France are established. 1251 is the year that Mindaugas of Lithuania is baptized, in prelude to his crowning as King of Lithuania in 1253. 1252 is the year that the Swedish city of Stockholm is founded by Birger Jarl. 1253 is the year that the Chinese era Baoyou begins in the Southern Song Dynasty of China. 1254 is the year that the Catholic dogma of purgatory is clarified and so named by the Catholic Church. 1255 is the year that Hulagu Khan is dispatched by his brother Möngke Khan to destroy the remaining Muslim states in southwestern Asia. 1256 is the year that the ancient Irish Kingdom of Breifne splits into East Breifne and West Breifne after a war between the O'Reillys and the O'Rourkes. 1257 is the year that the city of Kraków is rebuilt by Boleslaus V of Poland after being nearly destroyed in the Tatar invasions in 1241. 1258 is the year that Gissur Thorvaldsson is made Earl of Iceland by King Haakon IV of Norway. 1259 is the year that the Japanese Shōka era ends, and the Shōgen era begins. 1260 is the year that Nicola Pisano sculpts the pulpit of the Pisa Baptistery. 1261 is the year that Bela IV of Hungary repels a Tatar invasion. 1262 is the year that the Venetian Senate starts consolidating all of the city's outstanding debt into a single fund, later known as the Monte Vecchio. 1263 is the year that the doctrines of theologian Joachim of Fiore are condemned as heresy by the Roman Catholic Church at a synod in Arles. 1264 is the year that Thomas Aquinas completes his theological work Summa contra Gentiles. 1265 is the year that Pope Clement IV succeeds Pope Urban IV as the 183rd pope on February 5th. 1266 is the year that Mary de Ferrers is ordered to surrender land and Liverpool Castle to Edmund, second son of Henry III on July NaNth. 1267 is the year that Spain attempts an invasion of Morocco, but the Marinids successfully defend against the invasion and drive out Spanish forces. 1268 is the year that the county of Wernigerode becomes a vassal state of the margrave of Brandenburg. 1269 is the year that John Comyn begins the construction of Blair Castle in Scotland. 1270 is the year that Yekuno Amlak overthrows the Ethiopian Zagwe dynasty, claims the throne and establishes the Solomonic dynasty. 1271 is the year that Kublai Khan renames his empire "Yuan" (元 yuán), officially marking the start of the Yuan Dynasty of China on December 18th. 1272 is the year that Charles I of Anjou, King of Naples, occupies Durrës in Albania and establishes an Albanian kingdom. 1273 is the year that the 6-year-long battle of Xiangyang ends as the commander of the Song Dynasty's forces surrender to Kublai Khan's Yuan Dynasty on January 31st. 1274 is the year that the Marinid amir, Abu Yusuf Yaqub, enters peacefully into Ceuta putting an end to some forty years of independence of the city. 1275 is the year that Ramon Llull establishes a school in Majorca to teach Arabic to preachers in an attempt to aid proselytizing to Moors. 1276 is the year that Pope Innocent V succeeds Pope Gregory X as the 185th pope on January 21st. 1277 is the year that a number of philosophical doctrines such as Averroism are banned from Paris at a condemnation at the University of Paris. 1278 is the year that the earliest known written copy of the Avesta, a collection of ancient sacred Persian Zoroastrian texts previously passed down orally, is produced. 1279 is the year that the Chola Dynasty of South India falls under attacks by the Hoysala Empire and Pandyan Kingdom. 1280 is the year that the final expansion of the Lincoln Cathedral is completed. 1281 is the year that Niccolò Bonsignori heads a hundred of Ghibelline exiles in a failed attempt to topple the Sienese government on July NaNth. 1282 is the year that the technology of watermarks is introduced by paper manufacturers of Bologna, Italy. 1283 is the year that the city of Guiyang is founded in China. 1284 is the year that Mamluk sultan of Egypt Qalawun signs a 10-year truce with the Crusader city of Acre; he will violate the truce on pretexts in 1290. 1285 is the year that Roger of Lauria defeats King Philip III of France in a naval battle off of Barcelona on September 4th. 1286 is the year that the Guelph Republic of Siena allows exiled Ghibelline rebels back into the city. 1287 is the year that the Bruntal coat of arms makes its first appearance. 1288 is the year that the Flemish city of Ghent seeks rights to start redeeming its already issued annuities. 1289 is the year that the 5,452 meter (17,887 feet) high volcano Popocatépetl is first ascended by members of the Tecuanipas tribe in present-day Mexico. 1290 is the year that the founding Mamluk dynasty of the Sultanate of Delhi is overthrown by Jalal-ud-din Feroz Khalji of the Khilji dynasty. 1291 is the year that all glassmakers in Venice are forced to move to the island of Murano in order to contain the risk of fire, thus establishing the glass industry there. 1292 is the year that the Mongols land on Java, taking the capital, but it proves impossible to hold. 1293 is the year that the Japanese era Shōō ends, and the Einin era begins. 1294 is the year that Edward I of England and Philip the Fair of France declare war on each other. 1295 is the year that Marco Polo returns to Italy from his travels to China. 1296 is the year that Jalal ud din Firuz Khilji dies and Ala-Ud-Din-Khilji comes to the throne of the Delhi Sultanate in Hindustan. 1297 is the year that Monaco gains independence on January 8th. 1298 is the year that the foreign creditors of the Sienese Gran Tavola bank start demanding their deposits back thus accelerating the liquidity crisis faced by the firm. 1299 is the year that the city of Florence bans the use of Arabic numerals for commerce, allowing only Roman numerals.

1300 is the year that the Jubilee of Pope Boniface VIII is celebrated on February 22nd. 1301 is the year that Edward of Caernarvon (later King Edward II of England) becomes the first Prince of Wales on February 7th. 1302 is the year that Charles II of Naples makes peace with Frederick III of Sicily under the Treaty of Caltabellotta, ending the War of Sicilian Vespers on September 24th. 1303 is the year that the Khilji Dynasty under Alauddin Khilji conquers Chittorgarh in northern India, after taking the massive Chittorgarh Fort. 1304 is the year that the peace treaty signed between the khanates of the Mongol Empire. 1305 is the year that Philip IV of France accuses the Knights Templar of heresy. 1306 is the year that the Mongols raid India. 1307 is the year that William Tell shoots an apple off his son's head on November (according to legend) 18th. 1308 is the year that Emperor Hanazono ascends to the throne of Japan on December 28th. 1309 is the year that Alnwick Castle, Northumberland, is bought by the Percy family, later Earls of Northumberland. 1310 is the year that Abu al-Fida becomes governor of Hama. 1311 is the year that Bolingbroke Castle passes to the House of Lancaster. 1312 is the year that Pope Clement V forcibly disbands the Knights Templar on April NaNth. 1313 is the year that the Siege of Rostock ends. 1314 is the year that Louis IV elected Holy Roman Emperor on October NaNth. 1315 is the year that Adam Banastre, Henry de Lea and William Bradshaw attack Liverpool Castle on October 25th. 1316 is the year that the revolt of Llywelyn Bren breaks out in Wales on January 28th. 1317 is the year that Pope John XXII erects the dioceses of Luçon, Maillezais, and Tulle. 1318 is the year that Emperor Go-Daigo succeeds Emperor Hanazono on the throne of Japan. 1319 is the year that Upon the death of his maternal grandfather, King Haakon V, three-year-old Magnus Eriksson becomes King of Norway on May 8th. 1320 is the year that the Venetian Arsenal is rebuilt as the Arsenal Nuovo. 1321 is the year that Stefan Decanski becomes King of Serbia. 1322 is the year that Robert the Bruce of Scotland defeats King Edward II of England at Byland, forcing Edward to accept Scotland's independence on October 14th. 1323 is the year that the Treaty of Nöteborg between Sweden and the Novgorod Republic (Russia) is signed, regulating the border for the first time on August 12th. 1324 is the year that Defensor pacis is published by Marsilius of Padua. 1325 is the year that Muhammad bin Tughluq succeeds his father Ghiyath al-Din Tughluq as Sultan of Delhi. 1326 is the year that the foundation of Oriel College, Oxford, the University of Oxford's fifth oldest college, is confirmed by royal charter. 1327 is the year that Edward II is deposed by his wife Isabella on January 20th. 1328 is the year that Nicholas V is consecrated at St Peter's Basilica in Rome by the bishop of Venice on May 12th. 1329 is the year that David II becomes King of Scotland on June 7th. 1330 is the year that Vilnius, Lithuania receives its coat-of-arms, granted to the city in the seventh year of its existence. 1331 is the year that the Genkō War begins in Japan. 1332 is the year that Amda Seyon I, Emperor of Ethiopia begins his campaigns in the southern Muslim provinces (possibly in 1329) on February 18th. 1333 is the year that John of Drazic, bishop of Prague, founds a friary at Roudnice (Raudnitz). 1334 is the year that Pope Benedict XII succeeds Pope John XXII as the 197th pope on December 20th. 1335 is the year that Otto the Merry, Duke of Austria, becomes Duke of Carinthia on May 2nd. 1336 is the year that the Kemmu restoration ends and the Muromachi period begins in Japan. 1337 is the year that Edward, the Black Prince is crowned Duke of Cornwall on March 16th. 1338 is the year that Philip VI of France besieges Guienne in Southwest France and his navy attacks Portsmouth in England. 1339 is the year that Kashmir is conquered by Muslims. 1340 is the year that the Battle of Sluys is fought between the naval fleets of the Kingdom of England and the Kingdom of France on June 24th. 1341 is the year that Petrarch is crowned poet laureate in Rome, the first man since antiquity to be given this honor. 1342 is the year that Kitzbühel becomes part of Tyrol. 1343 is the year that the four Estonian kings are murdered at the negotiations with the Livonian Order on May 4th. 1344 is the year that the Compagnia dei Bardi in Florence goes bankrupt, along with the Peruzzi Bank and the Acciaiuoli Bank. 1345 is the year that the Miracle of the Host occurs (as commemorated in Amsterdam) on March 12th. 1346 is the year that Louis the Bavarian, challenger to Charles IV, is killed in a boar hunt, preventing civil war on October NaNth. 1347 is the year that the Byzantine civil war between John VI Kantakouzenos and the regency for John V Palaiologos ends with Kantakouzenos entering Constantinople on February 2nd. 1348 is the year that Charles University is founded in Prague on April 7th. 1349 is the year that Ibn Battuta arrives in Fez in Morocco. 1350 is the year that the Black Death first appears in Scotland. 1351 is the year that Firuz Tughlaq succeeds Mohammad Tughlaq as Sultan of Delhi. 1352 is the year that Moroccan traveller Ibn Battuta reports the existence of the ngoni and balafon instruments at the court of Mansa Musa. 1353 is the year that the Decameron is finished by Giovanni Boccaccio. 1354 is the year that the Treaty of Stralsund settles border disputes between the duchies of Mecklenburg and Pomerania on February 12th. 1355 is the year that the St. Scholastica's Day riot broke out in Oxford, England, leaving 63 scholars and perhaps 30 locals dead in two days on February 10th. 1356 is the year that Emperor Charles IV promulgates the Golden Bull, a sort of medieval constitution for the Holy Roman Empire on December 25th. 1357 is the year that Peter I becomes King of Portugal after the death of his father, Alfonso IV on May 28th. 1358 is the year that Muhammad II as Said becomes ruler of the Merinid Dynasty in present-day Morocco after the assassination of Abu Inan Faris. 1359 is the year that Upon the death of Erik Magnusson, his claims to the Swedish throne die with him and power is restored undivided to his father, king Magnus on June 21st. 1360 is the year that Dmitri Konstantinovich is installed as ruler of Vladimir (now in eastern Russia) by the Khan of the White Horde. 1361 is the year that Edward, the Black Prince, marries Joan, the 'Fair Maid of Kent' on October 10th. 1362 is the year that Lionel of Antwerp, son of King Edward III of England, is created Duke of Clarence on November NaNth. 1363 is the year that Philip the Bold becomes duke of Burgundy. 1364 is the year that the Ava Dynasty establish rule in present-day northern Burma. 1365 is the year that Mpu Prapanca writes the epic poem Nagarakretagama, about the Majapahit Empire in Java. 1366 is the year that the Stella Artois brewery is founded in present-day Belgium. 1367 is the year that a university is founded in pécs Hungary (not to be confused with the present University of Pécs, which was founded in 1921). 1368 is the year that Work begins on the current Great Wall of China. 1369 is the year that the Thai Kingdom of Ayutthaya conquers Cambodia for a second time. 1370 is the year that Pope Gregory XI succeeds Pope Urban V as the 201st pope on December 20th. 1371 is the year that Zhao Bing Fa becomes King of Mong Mao (in present day south China/north Myanmar) after the death of his father, Si Ke Fa. 1372 is the year that the Kingdom of Chūzan (now in southern Japan) enters tributary relations with Ming Dynasty China. 1373 is the year that the city of Phnom Penh (now the capital city of Cambodia) is founded. 1374 is the year that Musa II succeeds his father, Mari Djata II, as Mansa of the Mali Empire (now Mali & Senegal). 1375 is the year that Margaret I of Denmark becomes Regent of Denmark after the death of her father Valdemar IV on October NaNth. 1376 is the year that Pope Gregory XI excommunicates all members of the government of Florence and places the city under an interdict on March 31st. 1377 is the year that Pope Gregory XI moves the Papacy back from Avignon to Rome on January 17th. 1378 is the year that the Turks capture the town of Ihtiman in west Bulgaria. 1379 is the year that the Venetians and Ottomans invade Constantinople and restore John V Palaiologos as Byzantine co-emperor. 1380 is the year that Henry Bolingbroke marries Mary de Bohun at Arundel Castle on July 27th. 1381 is the year that Timur conquers east Persia, ending the rule of the Sarbadar Dynasty. 1382 is the year that Ahmad deposes his brother, Husain, as ruler of the Jalayirid dynasty in western Persia. 1383 is the year that Wat Phrathat Doi Suthep Temple is built in present-day Thailand by King Kuena of Lanna. 1384 is the year that Lisbon is besieged by the Castilian army, during the 1383-1385 Crisis on May–September NaNth. 1385 is the year that Charles VI of France marries Isabeau of Bavaria on July 17th. 1386 is the year that John of Gaunt leaves England to make good his claim to the throne of Castile by right of his second marriage to Constanza of Castile in 1371. 1387 is the year that Khan Tokhtamysh of the Golden Horde invades the Timurid Empire but has to soon after withdraw due to heavy snow. 1388 is the year that Ramesuan is reinstated as King of Ayutthaya (now southern Thailand) after dethroning and executing 17 year-old King Thong Chan. 1389 is the year that Hadji II is restored as Mamluk Sultan of Egypt after overthrowing Sultan Barquq. 1390 is the year that the Kingdom of Kaffa is established in present day Ethiopia (approximate date). 1391 is the year that the University of Ferrara is founded in present-day Italy. 1392 is the year that Queen Maria of Sicily defeats an army of rebel barons. 1393 is the year that Samsenethai succeeds his father, Fa Ngum, as King of Lan Xang (now Laos). 1394 is the year that Abd al-Aziz II succeeds Abu al-Abbas Ahmad II as ruler of the Hafsid dynasty in present-day Tunisia. 1395 is the year that the Principality of Monaco expels its Genoese occupiers and Jean I and Louis are crowned as joint Lords of Monaco. 1396 is the year that the Battle of the North Inch takes place in Perth, Scotland on September NaNth. 1397 is the year that Richard II of England attempts to reassert authority over his kingdom by arresting members of a group of powerful barons known as the Lords Appellant. 1398 is the year that Jianwen succeeds his grandfather, Hongwu, as Emperor of Ming Dynasty China. 1399 is the year that Thomas Arundel is restored as Archbishop of Canterbury, replacing Roger Walden.

1400 is the year that the Medici family becomes powerful in Florence. 1401 is the year that Grand Duke Vytautas of Lithuania is granted increased autonomy by King Jogaila of the Poland–Lithuania union. 1402 is the year that the rebel army of Zhu Di occupies the Ming Dynasty China capital Fengtian on July 12th. 1403 is the year that the world's first quarantine station is built in Venice to protect against the Black Death. 1404 is the year that Rebel leader Owain Glyndŵr, having declared himself Prince of Wales, allies with the French against the English on June 14th. 1405 is the year that Bellifortis, a book on military techonology, is published by Konrad Kyeser. 1406 is the year that Pope Gregory XII succeeds Pope Innocent VII as the 205th pope on November 30th. 1407 is the year that a solemn truce between John the Fearless, Duke of Burgundy and Louis of Valois, Duke of Orléans is agreed under the auspicies of John, Duke of Berry on November 20th. 1408 is the year that Henry, Prince of Wales (later Henry V of England) retakes Aberystwyth from Owain Glyndŵr. 1409 is the year that the University of Leipzig opens on December 2nd. 1410 is the year that Jan Hus is excommunicated by the Archbishop of Prague. 1411 is the year that the Battle of Harlaw is fought between Donald of Islay, Lord of the Isles and an army commanded by Alexander Stewart, Earl of Mar on July 24th. 1412 is the year that John II of Castile declares the Valladolid laws that restrict the social rights of Jews. 1413 is the year that Henry V becomes King of England on March 21st. 1414 is the year that Joan II succeeds her brother Ladislaus as Queen of Naples on August 6th. 1415 is the year that Frederick I becomes Elector of Brandenburg on April 30th. 1416 is the year that the Catholic Church burns Jerome of Prague as a heretic on May 30th. 1417 is the year that Pope Martin V succeeds Pope Gregory XII (who abdicated in 1415) as the 206th pope on November 11th. 1418 is the year that the first Portuguese settlers move to the Madeira Islands. 1419 is the year that the first Defenestration of Prague occurs on July 30th. 1420 is the year that the Madeira Islands are discovered by the Portuguese João Gonçalves Zarco. 1421 is the year that John III of Dampierre, Marquis of Namur, sells his estates to Philip the Good, Duke of Burgundy. 1422 is the year that the Siege of Meaux begins on March 21st. 1423 is the year that the three independent boroughs of Pamplona are united into a single town by royal decree after centuries of feuds. 1424 is the year that we do not know what happened. 1425 is the year that the Catholic University of Leuven, Belgium is founded. 1426 is the year that the Battle of Chirokitia is fought on July 7th. 1427 is the year that the first band of Gypsies visits Paris, according to an account of the citizen of Paris on August 17th. 1428 is the year that Itzcóatl becomes ruler of the Aztecs. 1429 is the year that Joan besieged La Charité on November 24th. 1430 is the year that the Janissaries are created. 1431 is the year that Pope Eugene IV succeeds Pope Martin V as the 207th pope on March 3rd. 1432 is the year that the Université de Caen is founded. 1433 is the year that Cosimo de' Medici, later the de facto ruler of Florence and patron of Marsilio Ficino, is exiled by the Albizzi/Strozzi faction on September NaNth. 1434 is the year that Cosimo de' Medici returns to Florence one year, to the day, following his exile by the Alberti and Strozzi faction on September NaNth. 1435 is the year that China returns to a policy of isolation. 1436 is the year that the Bosnian language is first mentioned in a document. 1437 is the year that James I of Scotland is stabbed on February 20th. 1438 is the year that Council of Florence is moved to Ferrara. 1439 is the year that the Great Ordinance is adopted by the French Estates-General. 1440 is the year that Itzcóatl, Aztec ruler of Tenochtitlan, dies and is succeeded by Moctezuma I (Moctezuma Ilhuicamina). 1441 is the year that Ouagadougou becomes the capital of the Mossi Kingdoms. 1442 is the year that Alfonso of Aragon is crowned at Naples on June 12th. 1443 is the year that Skanderbeg and his forces, rebelling against the Ottoman Empire, liberated Kruja, in Middle Albania, and raised the Albanian flag on November 28th. 1444 is the year that the first European slave market for the sale of African slaves, the Mercado de Escravos, opens in Lagos, Portugal. 1445 is the year that Senegal and Cape Verde are discovered by Dinas Diaz. 1446 is the year that Sultan Mehmed II of the Ottoman Empire is forced to abdicate in favor of his father Murad II by the Janissaries on Before October NaNth. 1447 is the year that Pope Nicholas V succeeds Pope Eugene IV as the 208th pope on March 6th. 1448 is the year that the Regency period of Sweden ends with the election of Karl Knutsson Bonde as King Charles VIII of Sweden on June 20th. 1449 is the year that Pope Nicholas V is elected by the Council of Basel on April 19th. 1450 is the year that the University of Barcelona is founded on November 3rd. 1451 is the year that Nicholas of Cusa invents concave lens spectacles to treat myopia. 1452 is the year that Murder of William Douglas, 8th Earl of Douglas by James II of Scotland at Stirling Castle on February 22nd. 1453 is the year that May 22– Partial lunar eclipse takes place. 1454 is the year that Casimir IV of Poland renounces allegiance to the Teutonic Knights on March 6th. 1455 is the year that Pope Calixtus III succeeds Pope Nicholas V as the 209th pope on April 8th. 1456 is the year that a retrial acquits Joan of Arc of heresy 25 years after her death on July 7th. 1457 is the year that the oldest printed book to carry a date, the Mainz Psalter, is published. 1458 is the year that the Jewish community is expelled from Erfurt (Germany), their houses are sold and the synagogue turned into an arsenal. 1459 is the year that the Wallachian town of Bucharest is first mentioned. 1460 is the year that the cannon of the Tower of London, still in Lancaster hands, are fired on the city of London, which is mostly in Yorkist hands on July 4th. 1461 is the year that Louis XI of France succeeds Charles VII of France as king (reigns until 1483). 1462 is the year that Vasili II of Russia dies, and is succeeded by his son Ivan III of Russia on March 27th. 1463 is the year that Poet François Villon is banned from Paris on January 5th. 1464 is the year that Pope Pius II himself shoulders the cross of the Crusader. 1465 is the year that Amadeus IX becomes Duke of Savoy on January 29th. 1466 is the year that Louis XI of France introduces silk weaving to Lyon. 1467 is the year that Regent of Sweden Erik Axelsson Tott supports the re-election of deposed Charles VIII of Sweden to the throne. 1468 is the year that Metz Cathedral is completed. 1469 is the year that Moctezuma I, Aztec ruler of Tenochtitlan, dies and is succeeded by Axayacatl. 1470 is the year that Johann Heynlin introduces the printing press into France and prints his first book that same year. 1471 is the year that the Yorkist King Edward IV returns to England to reclaim his throne on March NaNth. 1472 is the year that Fernão do Po claims the central-African islands Bioko and Annobón for Portugal. 1473 is the year that First complete printed edition of Avicenna's The Canon of Medicine (in Latin translation) published in Milan on February 12th. 1474 is the year that the Earth probably went around the Sun. 1475 is the year that August 29— The Treaty of Picquigny ends a brief war between France and England. 1476 is the year that nothing interesting came to pass. 1477 is the year that William Caxton produces Dictes or Sayengis of the Philosophres, the first English book printed on an English printing press on November 18th. 1478 is the year that Vladislav II of Bohemia makes peace with Hungary. 1479 is the year that Ferdinand II ascends the throne of Aragon and rules together with his wife Isabella I, Queen of Castile over most of the Iberian peninsula on January 20th. 1480 is the year that an Ottoman army lands near Otranto, Italy on July 28th. 1481 is the year that Ludovico Sforza emerges as Regent of Milan (until 1499). 1482 is the year that Ivan III renounces the Mongol Khanate rule over Russia. 1483 is the year that a rebellion by the Duke of Buckingham is crushed by Richard III on October NaNth. 1484 is the year that the King of Portugal appoints a commission of mathematicians to perfect tables to help seamen find their latitude. 1485 is the year that the Peace of Bourges freezes the Mad War on November 2nd. 1486 is the year that Giovanni Pico della Mirandola returns to Florence and writes Oration on the Dignity of Man. 1487 is the year that the witch-hunters' manual Malleus Maleficarum is published. 1488 is the year that Jasper Tudor, 1st Duke of Bedford, takes possession of Cardiff Castle. 1489 is the year that Nicosia, Cyprus, becomes a possession of Venice. 1490 is the year that all Saints' Church, the Schlosskirche in Wittenberg is begun. 1491 is the year that Nicolaus Copernicus enters Kraków University. 1492 is the year that Christopher Columbus lands in Cuba on October 28th. 1493 is the year that Christopher Columbus returns to Spain from his first voyage of discovery on March 15th. 1494 is the year that Alfonso II becomes King of Naples on January 25th. 1495 is the year that Henry VII of England commissions the world's first dry dock at Portsmouth. 1496 is the year that Leonardo da Vinci unsuccessfully tests a flying machine on January 3rd. 1497 is the year that Ivan the Great issues his law code, the Sudebnik. 1498 is the year that Girolamo Savonarola, ruler of Florence, is executed for criticizing the Pope on May 23rd. 1499 is the year that Pretender to the throne Perkin Warbeck is hanged for reportedly attempting to escape from the Tower of London on November 23rd.

1500 is the year that Emperor Go-Kashiwabara accedes to the throne of Japan on November 16th. 1501 is the year that Czar Ivan III of Russia invades Lithuania. 1502 is the year that the King's School in Macclesfield is founded by Sir John Percyvale. 1503 is the year that Pope Julius II succeeds Pius III as the 216th pope (some sources list November 1 as the date of election) on October 31st. 1504 is the year that Isabella I of Castile signs her testament on October 12th. 1505 is the year that Bermuda is discovered by Spanish explorer Juan de Bermúdez. 1506 is the year that Pope Julius II lays the foundation stone of the new (current) St. Peter's Basilica, replacing the Old Saint Peter's Basilica on April 18th. 1507 is the year that Cardinal Cisneros is appointed major inquisitor of Castile. 1508 is the year that Michelangelo Buonarroti begins work on the ceiling of the Sistine Chapel on December NaNth. 1509 is the year that Henry VIII of England marries Catherine of Aragon. 1510 is the year that Afonso de Albuquerque of Portugal conquers Goa on February 27th. 1511 is the year that Erasmus publishes his most famous work, The Praise of Folly, as Moriae encomium / Laus stultitiae. 1512 is the year that Martin Luther becomes a doctor of theology (Doctor in Biblia) on October 19th. 1513 is the year that the dispute between Johann Reuchlin and Johannes Pfefferkorn, relative to the Talmud and other Jewish books, is referred to Pope Leo X on September NaNth. 1514 is the year that a huge exotic embassy sent by King Manuel I of Portugal to Pope Leo X defiles in Rome on March 12th. 1515 is the year that Dürer's Rhinoceros cut. 1516 is the year that the Reinheitsgebot is instituted in Ingolstadt, Bavaria, regulating the purity of beer permissible for sale on April 23rd. 1517 is the year that Selim I, Sultan of the Ottoman Empire, conquers Egypt and declares himself Caliph. 1518 is the year that the Treaty of London temporarily ensures peace in Western Europe on October 3rd. 1519 is the year that Hernán Cortés and his men, accompanied by 3,000 Tlaxcalans, entered Cholula on October 12th. 1520 is the year that Martin Luther writes To the Christian Nobility of the German Nation. 1521 is the year that the Diet of Worms begins, lasting until May 25 on January 28th. 1522 is the year that the Turks finally break into Rhodes, but the Knights continue fierce resistance in the streets on December 18th. 1523 is the year that Pope Clement VII succeeds Pope Adrian VI as the 219th pope on November 19th. 1524 is the year that Francisco Hernandez de Cordoba founds the city of Granada, Nicaragua, the oldest Hispanic city in the mainland of the Western Hemisphere on December 8th. 1525 is the year that the first French ambassador arrives in Istanbul. 1526 is the year that Milan is captured by the Spanish on July 24th. 1527 is the year that Paracelsus is appointed as town physician of Basle on March NaNth. 1528 is the year that the fourth major outbreak of the sweating sickness occurs in England. 1529 is the year that Paracelsus uses the name Paracelsus for the first time. 1530 is the year that Humayun starts to rule. 1531 is the year that the city of Puebla, Mexico is founded on April 16th. 1532 is the year that Francisco Pizarro lands on the northern coast of Peru on May 13th. 1533 is the year that Francisco Pizarro arrives in Cuzco, Peru on November 15th. 1534 is the year that Pope Paul III succeeds Pope Clement VII as the 220th pope on October 13th. 1535 is the year that Fray Tomás de Berlanga discovers the Galápagos Islands when blown off course en route to Peru on March 10th. 1536 is the year that Cristobal de Onate founds San Juan Bautista del Teul on June 24th. 1537 is the year that the island of Paros is conquered by the Ottoman Empire. 1538 is the year that Paracelsus visits Villach. 1539 is the year that Horse racing begins at Chester. 1540 is the year that Coronado captures Hawikuh, then known as part of Cíbola, but fails to find the legendary gold on July 7th. 1541 is the year that an Algerian military campaign by Charles V of Spain (Habsburg) is unsuccessful on October NaNth. 1542 is the year that Queen Mary, Queen of Scots, becomes queen at the age of only one week on December 14th. 1543 is the year that the Japanese receive the first firearms from shipwrecked Portuguese. 1544 is the year that Emperor Charles V again invades eastern France on May NaNth. 1545 is the year that the Council of Trent officially opens (closes 1563) on December 13th. 1546 is the year that Treaty of Ardres, also known as the Treaty of Camp, is signed, resulting in peace between England and France on June 7th. 1547 is the year that Edward VI of England is crowned at Westminster Abbey on February 20th. 1548 is the year that a marriage treaty is signed between Scotland and France, whereby 5-year-old Mary, Queen of Scots, is betrothed to the future King Francis II of France on July 7th. 1549 is the year that the city of Salvador da Bahia, Brazil's first capital, is founded on March 29th. 1550 is the year that Pope Julius III succeeds Pope Paul III as the 221st pope on February 8th. 1551 is the year that the Royal and Pontifical University of Mexico is founded in Mexico City (Mexico), being the second officially established university in the Americas on September 21st. 1552 is the year that Henry II of France and Maurice of Saxony sign the Treaty of Chambord on January 15th. 1553 is the year that Christ's Hospital and King Edward's School, Witley, England, are created by Royal Charter on June 26th. 1554 is the year that Mary of Guise becomes Regent of Scotland on April 12th. 1555 is the year that Pope Paul IV creates the first Jewish ghetto in Rome on July 12th. 1556 is the year that Archbishop of Canterbury Thomas Cranmer is declared a heretic. 1557 is the year that Mary I of England joins her husband Philip II of Spain in his war against France on June 7th. 1558 is the year that Queen Elizabeth grants rest and refreshment to pilgrims and travellers who pass by the Holy Well Spring, Malvern. 1559 is the year that John Knox returns from exile to Scotland to become the leader of the beginning Scottish Reformation on May 2nd. 1560 is the year that the first scientific society, the Academia Secretorum Naturae, is founded in Naples by Giambattista della Porta. 1561 is the year that the first Calvinists settle in England after fleeing Flanders. 1562 is the year that Akbar the Great conquers Malwa and defeats Baz Bahadur. 1563 is the year that the outbreak of the Northern Seven Years' War on August 13th. 1564 is the year that the modern pencil becomes common in England. 1565 is the year that the pencil is first documented by Conrad Gesner. 1566 is the year that Pope Pius V expels most the prostitutes from Rome. 1567 is the year that Henry Stuart, Lord Darnley, husband of Mary, Queen of Scots, is murdered at the Provost's House in Edinburgh on February 10th. 1568 is the year that William I of Orange invades the Southeastern Netherlands on October 5th. 1569 is the year that the first recorded lottery in England is performed nonstop at the west door of the St. Paul's Cathedral on January–May 6 11th. 1570 is the year that the Andean population of Peru reaches 1.3 million. 1571 is the year that the Spanish occupy Manila, Philippines. 1572 is the year that a large Crimean Tatar–Ottoman army which invaded Russia is routed in the battle of Molodi on July–August 2 29th. 1573 is the year that Wanli starts to rule in China. 1574 is the year that the fifth War of Religion against the Huguenots begins in France on February 23rd. 1575 is the year that Queen Elizabeth I of England grants a monopoly on producing printed sheet music to Thomas Tallis and William Byrd. 1576 is the year that an early example of autobiography is written in English by Thomas Wythorne. 1577 is the year that the church in San Pedro de Atacama is built in the Atacama Desert in Chile . 1578 is the year that Martin Frobisher sails from Harwich, England to Frobisher Bay, Canada, eventually to mine fool's gold, used to pave streets in London on May 31st. 1579 is the year that Maastricht is captured by the Spanish under Parma on March NaNth. 1580 is the year that the Ostrog Bible, the first complete printed Bible in a Slavic language, is published on July 12th. 1581 is the year that Yermak begins the Russian conquest of the Khanate of Sibir with a band of 1,636 men on Summer (probable) NaNth. 1582 is the year that Kumbum is founded in Tibet. 1583 is the year that François, Duke of Anjou, attacks Antwerp on January 18th. 1584 is the year that Ghent falls into the hands of Alexander Farnese, governor of the Spanish Netherlands on September 17th. 1585 is the year that John Davis enters Cumberland Sound in his quest for the Northwest Passage on August 8th. 1586 is the year that the reign of Emperor Ogimachi of Japan ends and Emperor Go-Yozei ascends to the throne of Japan on December 17th. 1587 is the year that a severe famine breaks out in China during the Ming Dynasty. 1588 is the year that the English and Spanish fleets meet again off Dorset (The English fleet is led by Lord Howard of Effingham and Sir Francis Drake) on August 2nd. 1589 is the year that the monks of the Pechenga Monastery, the northernmost in the world, are massacred by the Swedes. 1590 is the year that Japan is united by Toyotomi Hideyoshi. 1591 is the year that Hulst is captured by Maurice on September 14th. 1592 is the year that the Battle of Okpo is another naval victory for Korea over Japan on May 7th. 1593 is the year that Henry Constable's Spiritual Sonnetts are written. 1594 is the year that Sir Richard Hawkins arrives in the Bay of San Mateo, where he is attacked and captured by two Spanish ships on June NaNth. 1595 is the year that Mehmed III succeeds Murad III as Sultan of the Ottoman Empire. 1596 is the year that an English fleet, commanded by Robert Devereux, 2nd Earl of Essex, and Lord Howard of Effingham, sacks Cádiz on July 5th. 1597 is the year that Tycho Brahe's stipend is stopped on March 18th. 1598 is the year that Philip III of Spain starts to rule on September 13th. 1599 is the year that a Persian embassy arrives in Moscow on November NaNth.

1600 is the year that Sebald de Weert makes the first definite sighting of the Falkland Islands on January NaNth. 1601 is the year that France gains Bresse, Bugey and Gex from Savoy, ceding Saluzzo in exchange on January 17th. 1602 is the year that Bartolomew Gosnold becomes the first European at Cape Cod on May 15th. 1603 is the year that Samuel de Champlain returns to France on August NaNth. 1604 is the year that Za Dengel is deposed as Emperor of Ethiopia by Za Sellase, who restores his cousin Yaqob. 1605 is the year that Jahangir begins his 22-year reign of the Mughal Empire on November 3rd. 1606 is the year that the Evangelic Lyceum (Evanjelické lýceum), a Lutheran high school is founded in Bratislava. 1607 is the year that Jamestown, is settled as what would become the first permanent English colony in North America on May 14th. 1608 is the year that John Smith is elected council president of Jamestown, and begins expanding the fort on September 10th. 1609 is the year that Cornelius Drebbel invents the thermostat. 1610 is the year that the Orion Nebula is discovered by Nicolas-Claude Fabri de Peiresc. 1611 is the year that Yemana Kristos, brother of Emperor Susenyos, ends the rebellion of Melka Sedeq in the Battle of Segaba in Begemder on March 9th. 1612 is the year that a Sicilian–Neapolitan galley fleet defeats the Tunisians at La Goulette on May–May 25 23rd. 1613 is the year that the Earl of Somerset marries Frances Howard, occasioning John Donne's Eclogue on December 26th. 1614 is the year that the Siege of Osaka begins on December 4th. 1615 is the year that the Peace of Tyrnau is signed between Holy Roman Emperor Matthias and Gábor Bethlen on May 6th. 1616 is the year that Gustavus Adolphus (1611–1632), trained, since childhood, to become the Swedish king, begins to accompany the army on campaigns. 1617 is the year that the Treaty of Stolbovo ends the Ingrian War between Sweden and Russia on February 27th. 1618 is the year that the Ming Chinese embassy of the Wanli Emperor presents tea to the Russian tsar. 1619 is the year that the Banqueting House of James I of England is destroyed by fire. 1620 is the year that Cornelius Drebbel, at the Thames, builds an undersea boat (history of submarines). 1621 is the year that the Swedish king Gustav II Adolf grants city rights to Luleå, Piteå and Torneå (Tornio). 1622 is the year that Albertus Magnus is beatified, and Teresa of Avila is canonized, by the Roman Catholic Church. 1623 is the year that Première of Pedro Calderón de la Barca's first play, Amor, honor y poder, at the Court of Habsburg Spain on June 29th. 1624 is the year that the Netherlands establishes a trading colony at Tainan on Taiwan. 1625 is the year that the Dutch settle Manhattan, founding the town of New Amsterdam. 1626 is the year that Peter Minuit buys Manhattan from a Native American tribe (Lenape or Shinnecock or Canarsie) for trade goods, valued at 60 guilders ("$24") on May 24th. 1627 is the year that the English, under the Duke of Buckingham, invade Ré Island in support of the Huguenots in La Rochelle on July 22nd. 1628 is the year that Shah Jahan crowned as ruler of the Mughal Empire in Agra on January 25th. 1629 is the year that Emperor Go-Mizunoo of Japan abdicates the throne in favour of his daughter, who becomes Empress Meishō on November 8th. 1630 is the year that the first account of the Childes Tomb story is published. 1631 is the year that Mount Vesuvius erupts in Pompeii. 1632 is the year that Fasilides succeeds his father Susenyos as Emperor of Ethiopia. 1633 is the year that Samuel de Champlain reclaims his role as commander of New France on behalf of Cardinal Richelieu on March 1st. 1634 is the year that the Burchardi flood (also known as the second Grote Mandrenke) strikes the North Sea coast of Germany and Denmark, causing 8,000–12,000 deaths on October–October 12 11th. 1635 is the year that the Académie française in Paris is formally constituted as the national academy for the preservation of the French language on February 22nd. 1636 is the year that the Shogun forbids Japanese to travel abroad and those abroad from returning home. 1637 is the year that Ferdinand III becomes the Holy Roman Emperor on February 15th. 1638 is the year that the Swedish arrive on the ships Kalmar Nyckel and Fogel Grip to America, to establish the first settlement in Delaware, called New Sweden on March 29th. 1639 is the year that the first of the Bishops' Wars breaks out between Charles I and Scotland on May NaNth. 1640 is the year that the Guerra dels Segadors breaks out in Catalonia on May 22nd. 1641 is the year that the Norwegian city of Kristiansand is founded by King Christian IV. 1642 is the year that the Dutch drive Spain from Taiwan. 1643 is the year that Miyamoto Musashi dictates The Book of Five Rings (Go Rin No Sho) to his student, completing it in 1654 just before his death. 1644 is the year that Explorer Abel Tasman's second expedition for the Dutch East India Company maps the north coast of Australia on February–August NaNth. 1645 is the year that the Long Parliament outlaws the 1559 version of the Book of Common Prayer. 1646 is the year that the first Protestant church assembly for natives is held in Massachusetts (see Waban) on October 28th. 1647 is the year that Aberystwyth Castle is razed to the ground by Parliamentarian troops. 1648 is the year that the First Fronde, the Fronde Parlementaire, an insurrection, begins in France. 1649 is the year that January 30 Charles I is beheaded for treason, outside the Banqueting Hall in the Palace of Whitehall, London. 1650 is the year that the New Model Army is decimated at the Siege of Clonmel on May NaNth. 1651 is the year that the Keian Uprising fails in Japan. 1652 is the year that Rhode Island passes the first law in North America making slavery illegal on May 18th. 1653 is the year that Cardinal Mazarin returns to Paris from exile on February 3rd. 1654 is the year that Ferdinand Maria, Elector of Bavaria is crowned on October 31st. 1655 is the year that Lord Protector Oliver Cromwell divides England into 11 districts under major-generals on August 9th. 1656 is the year that the ship Vergulde Draeck is wrecked off Ledge Point, Western Australia after it departs the Cape of Good Hope; rescue missions fail to find survivors on April 28th. 1657 is the year that the Flushing Remonstrance is signed in New Amsterdam at the site of the future (1862) Flushing Town Hall in New York on December 27th. 1658 is the year that Sarhuda's Manchu fleet annihilates Onufriy Stepanov's Russian flotilla on the Amur on July NaNth. 1659 is the year that Peter Stuyvesant of New Netherland forbids tennis playing during religious services (first mention of tennis in what will be the U.S.) on September 30th. 1660 is the year that Charles XI becomes king of Sweden upon the death of his father, Charles X Gustavus on February 13th. 1661 is the year that the Shunzhi Emperor of the Qing Dynasty of China dies and is succeeded by his son the Kangxi Emperor on February 5th. 1662 is the year that Samuel Pepys witnesses a Punch and Judy show in London (the first on record) on May 9th. 1663 is the year that the first Maroon community arises in Suriname. 1664 is the year that New Jersey becomes a colony of England on March 12th. 1665 is the year that the University of Kiel is founded on October 5th. 1666 is the year that the Great Fire of London ends on September 5th. 1667 is the year that the War of Devolution begins; France invades Flanders and Franche-Comté on May 24th. 1668 is the year that Bishop Isaac Barrow founds the Bishop Barrow Trust to establish a university on the Isle of Man (King William's College). 1669 is the year that Phosphorus is discovered by Hennig Brand. 1670 is the year that September 5 – William Penn and William Mead are tried in London for preaching a Quaker sermon on September 1st. 1671 is the year that the Ottoman Empire declares war on Poland on June 22nd. 1672 is the year that Charles II of England issues the Royal Declaration of Indulgence on March 15th. 1673 is the year that France begins its expedition against Ceylon. 1674 is the year that England and the Netherlands sign the Treaty of Westminster on February 19th. 1675 is the year that Gottfried Leibniz uses infinitesimal calculus on a function. 1676 is the year that Edmond Halley observes the transit of Venus. 1677 is the year that Elias Ashmole gifts the collection that begins the Ashmolean Museum to Oxford University. 1678 is the year that John Bunyan publishes his novel, The Pilgrim's Progress on February 18th. 1679 is the year that the city of Duluth, Minnesota is founded. 1680 is the year that the Reverend Ralph Davenant dies, leaving £100 in his will to start up a new school for the poor boys of Whitechapel, in the East End on February NaNth. 1681 is the year that Titus Oates is told to leave his state apartments in the Whitehall; his fame begins to wane and he is soon arrested and imprisoned for sedition on August 31st. 1682 is the year that the Royal Chelsea Hospital for Soldiers is founded in England on March 11th. 1683 is the year that the Rye House Plot to assassinate Charles II of England is discovered on June 12th. 1684 is the year that John Bunyan writes The Pilgrim's Progress, Part 2. 1685 is the year that Louis XIV of France passes the "Code Noir", allowing the full use of slaves in the French colonies on March NaNth. 1686 is the year that a hurricane saves Charleston, South Carolina, from attack by Spanish vessels. 1687 is the year that the men under explorer Robert Cavelier de La Salle murder him while searching for the mouth of the Mississippi River on March 19th. 1688 is the year that Fire destroys Bungay in England. 1689 is the year that William III and Mary II are proclaimed co-rulers of England, Scotland and Ireland on February 13th. 1690 is the year that Earliest recorded sighting of the planet Uranus, by John Flamsteed, who mistakenly catalogues it as the star 34 Tauri on December NaNth. 1691 is the year that the Khalkha submit to the Manchu invaders, bringing most of modern-day Mongolia under the rule of the Qing dynasty. 1692 is the year that Salem witch trial investigations and convictions lead to several months of hangings on June 10th. 1693 is the year that the College of William and Mary in Williamsburg, Virginia is granted a Royal charter from King William III and Queen Mary II of England on February 8th. 1694 is the year that the colony Quilombo dos Palmares, Brazil is destroyed on February 6th. 1695 is the year that Gold is discovered in Brazil. 1696 is the year that Colley Cibber's play Love's Last Shift is performed at the Theatre Royal. 1697 is the year that the use of palanquins increases in Europe. 1698 is the year that the Abenaki tribe and the Massachusetts colonists sign a treaty ending the conflict in New England on January 1st. 1699 is the year that the 10th Sikh Master, Guru Gobind Singh, creates the Khalsa on April 13th.

1700 is the year that a Russian army invades Estonia and besieges the town of Narva on Late summer NaNth. 1701 is the year that Jethro Tull (agriculturist) invented a drill for planting seeds in rows. 1702 is the year that Queen Anne's Captain-General John Churchill forces the surrender of Kaiserswerth on the Rhine on June NaNth. 1703 is the year that the Company of Quenching of Fire (i.e., a fire brigade) is founded in Edinburgh, Scotland on April 21st. 1704 is the year that Rome decrees that Roman ceremonial practice in Latin (not in Chinese) is to be the law for Chinese missions. 1705 is the year that the Sophia Naturalization Act is passed by the English Parliament, which naturalizes Sophia of Hanover and the "issue of her body" as English subjects on December NaNth. 1706 is the year that the Earth probably went around the Sun. 1707 is the year that the Parliament of the Kingdom of Great Britain first meets in London on October 23rd. 1708 is the year that James Francis Edward Stuart unsuccessfully tries to land at the Firth of Forth on March 23rd. 1709 is the year that Abraham Darby I successfully produces cast iron using coke fuel at his Coalbrookdale blast furnace in Shropshire, England on January 10th. 1710 is the year that St. Francis Abbey Brewery, Kilkenny, Ireland is founded by John Smithwick, the home of Smithwick's Ale. 1711 is the year that Tuscarora natives capture John Lawson, Christoph von Graffenried and their expeditionary party and bring them to Catechna (approximate date) on September 14th. 1712 is the year that the VOC Zuytdorp is wrecked off the coast of Western Australia. 1713 is the year that Frederick William I of Prussia begins his reign on February 25th. 1714 is the year that the Duchy of Savoy and Piedmont becomes the Kingdom of Sardinia. 1715 is the year that a Spanish treasure fleet of 10 ships under General Don Juan Ubilla leaves Havana, Cuba for Spain on July 24th. 1716 is the year that Pirate Blackbeard (Edward Teach) raids shipping in the Caribbean. 1717 is the year that a disastrous flood hits the North Sea coast between the Netherlands and Denmark; thousands die or lose their houses on December–December 25 24th. 1718 is the year that the white potato reaches New England from England. 1719 is the year that Andrew Bradford publishes the American Weekly Mercury, Pennsylvania's first newspaper on December 22nd. 1720 is the year that Edmond Halley is appointed as Astronomer Royal. 1721 is the year that the Treaty of Nystad is signed, ending the Great Northern War on September 10th. 1722 is the year that William Battin, 17, is hanged for arson and murder in the colony of Pennsylvania on August 15th. 1723 is the year that the Four Seasons, a set of violin concertos by Antonio Vivaldi, was composed. 1724 is the year that Joseph Blake (alias Blueskin), highwayman, is hanged in London on November 11th. 1725 is the year that Jonathan Wild, fraudulent "Thief-Taker General", is hanged in Tyburn, England for actually aiding criminals on May 24th. 1726 is the year that Pirate Nicholas Brown captured near Xtabi, Jamaica on August 7th. 1727 is the year that Ursuline Academy is founded by the Sisters of the Order of Saint Ursula in New Orleans. 1728 is the year that Voltaire ends his exile in England on Late Summer NaNth. 1729 is the year that Putney Bridge was built. 1730 is the year that Anna Ivanovna (Anna of Russia) becomes tsarina, following the death of her cousin, Tsar Peter II on January 29th. 1731 is the year that John Bevis observes the Crab Nebula for the first time. 1732 is the year that James Oglethorpe is granted a royal charter for the colony of Georgia on June 9th. 1733 is the year that the election of Augustus III to succeed his father as King of Poland sparks the War of the Polish Succession on October 5th. 1734 is the year that the Dzików Confederation is created in Poland on November 5th. 1735 is the year that a shipbuilding industry begins in Mumbai. 1736 is the year that Bushehr is founded in Persia. 1737 is the year that the oldest existing English language newspaper in the world, The (Belfast) News Letter, is founded in Ireland. 1738 is the year that Court Jew Joseph Suss Oppenheimer is executed in Württemberg on February 4th. 1739 is the year that the British capture the South American silver exporting town of Portobelo from the Spanish on November 21st. 1740 is the year that University of Pennsylvania is founded. 1741 is the year that Vitus Bering dies in his expedition east of Siberia on December 19th. 1742 is the year that the University of Erlangen is founded. 1743 is the year that Natalia Lopukhina is flogged in front of the Twelve Collegia building in Saint Petersburg on September 11th. 1744 is the year that the third French and Indian War, known as King George's War, breaks out at Port Royal, Nova Scotia. 1745 is the year that Madame de Pompadour is officially presented in the court of Louis XV of France on September 14th. 1746 is the year that the town of Vilkovo (Odes'ka oblast', Ukraine) is founded. 1747 is the year that Emperor Momozono ascends to the throne of Japan, succeeding Emperor Sakuramachi on June 9th. 1748 is the year that Louis XV of France authorizes a 5% income tax on every individual regardless of social status; the Parlement of Paris protests. 1749 is the year that the first official performance of George Frideric Handel's Music for the Royal Fireworks finishes early due to the outbreak of fire on April 27th. 1750 is the year that Maruyama Okyo paints The Ghost of Oyuki. 1751 is the year that University of Glasgow School of Medicine is founded. 1752 is the year that the Virginia Assembly passes a law making maiming a felony, in response to the practice of gouging on February 27th. 1753 is the year that the founding charter of the British Museum is enacted on April 5th. 1754 is the year that Columbia University is founded as King's College by royal charter of King George II of England on July NaNth. 1755 is the year that the Great Expulsion of the Acadians begins on August NaNth. 1756 is the year that a garrison of the British Army in India is imprisoned in the Black Hole of Calcutta on 20 June 20th. 1757 is the year that Emanuel Swedenborg claims to have witnessed the Last Judgement occurring in the spiritual world. 1758 is the year that First European settlement in what is now Erie County by the French at the mouth of Buffalo Creek. 1759 is the year that the Famous Guinness Brewery is founded in St. James's Gate, Dublin Ireland. 1760 is the year that the town (later city) of Mayagüez, Puerto Rico, is founded on September 18th. 1761 is the year that an earthquake in London breaks chimneys in Limehouse and Poplar on February 8th. 1762 is the year that Louis XV orders the construction of the Petit Trianon, in the park of the Palace of Versailles, for his mistress Madame de Pompadour. 1763 is the year that Joseph Haydn wrote Symphony No. 1764 is the year that the Sugar Act is passed on April 6th. 1765 is the year that the first chocolate factory in the United States is established by Dr. James Baker at Dorchester, Massachusetts. 1766 is the year that Wolfgang Amadeus Mozart returns to Salzburg after touring Paris and London with his father. 1767 is the year that Pitcairn Island is first definitely sighted by Midshipman Robert Pitcairn on an expeditionary voyage commanded by Philip Carteret. 1768 is the year that Bougainville Strait was discovered. 1769 is the year that Frontiersman Daniel Boone first begins to explore the present-day Bluegrass State, Kentucky on June 7th. 1770 is the year that Joseph Priestley, British chemist, recommends the use of a rubber to remove pencil marks. 1771 is the year that the Dutch merchant ship Vrouw Maria sinks off the coast of Finland; Captain Raymund Lourens and his crew escape unharmed on October 9th. 1772 is the year that Johann Friedrich Struensee and Queen Caroline Matilda are arrested, leading to his execution and her banishment from Denmark on January 17th. 1773 is the year that Friedrich Gottlieb Klopstock publishes the last five cantos of his epic poem Der Messias in Hamburg. 1774 is the year that the British pass the Quebec Act, setting out rules of governance for the colony of Quebec in British North America on June 22nd. 1775 is the year that Pope Pius VI succeeds Pope Clement XIV as the 250th pope on February 15th. 1776 is the year that the Phi Beta Kappa society is founded at the College of William and Mary on December 5th. 1777 is the year that American Revolution – British troops occupy Philadelphia during the Revolutionary War on September 26th. 1778 is the year that the Treaty of Fort Pitt is signed, the first formal treaty between the United States and a Native American tribe (the Lenape or Delaware) on September 17th. 1779 is the year that the Iron Bridge is completed across the River Severn in Shropshire (the first all cast-iron bridge ever constructed). 1780 is the year that the original Craven Cottage is built by William Craven, 6th Baron Craven (located on the centre circle of the pitch). 1781 is the year that an army sent from Lima put down the rebellions and captures and savagely execute Túpac Amaru II on May 18th. 1782 is the year that the Spanish defeat British forces and capture Minorca. 1783 is the year that the Waterford Glassware Factory begins production in Waterford City, Ireland on October 3rd. 1784 is the year that Antoine Lavoisier pioneers quantitative chemistry. 1785 is the year that the University of New Brunswick is founded in Fredericton, New Brunswick, Canada. 1786 is the year that Goethe undertakes his Italian Journey (published in 1817) on September–December NaNth. 1787 is the year that Washington Academy (now Washington & Jefferson College) was chartered by the Pennsylvania General Assembly on September 24th. 1788 is the year that the Royal Dramatic Theatre (Kungliga Dramatiska Teatern), Sweden's national drama company, is founded on May 10th. 1789 is the year that William Herschel discovers Enceladus, one of Saturn's moons on August 28th. 1790 is the year that Louis XVI of France declares to the National Assembly that he will maintain the constitutional laws on February 4th. 1791 is the year that the French Royal Family is captured when they try to flee in disguise on June 20th. 1792 is the year that Prussia declares war against France. 1793 is the year that George Washington holds the first Cabinet meeting as President of the United States on February 25th. 1794 is the year that Bowdoin College is founded. 1795 is the year that the 11th Amendment to the United States Constitution is passed on February 7th. 1796 is the year that the capital of Upper Canada is moved from Newark to York on February 1st. 1797 is the year that the Treaty of Campo Formio ends the War of the First Coalition on October 17th. 1798 is the year that the papacy is removed from power by French General Louis Alexandre Berthier on February 10th. 1799 is the year that the British and Russians send an expedition to the Batavian Republic (now the Netherlands) on August 27th.

1800 is the year that U.S. President John Adams becomes the first President of the United States to live in the Executive Mansion (later renamed the White House). 1801 is the year that Tsar Paul I of Russia is murdered on March 23rd. 1802 is the year that Thomas Wedgwood publishes an account of his experiments in photography, along with Humphry Davy. 1803 is the year that the First Consul of France Citizen Bonaparte begins making preparations to invade England on May NaNth. 1804 is the year that Alexander Hamilton is shot during a duel with Aaron Burr and dies the next day on July 11th. 1805 is the year that the Harmony Society is officially formed on February 15th. 1806 is the year that the British occupy the Cape of Good Hope on January 19th. 1807 is the year that the municipality of Mogpog in Marinduque, Philippines is founded. 1808 is the year that the original Covent Garden Theatre in London is destroyed by a fire, along with most of the scenery, costumes and scripts on December 20th. 1809 is the year that Sweden promulgates a new Instrument of Government, which restores political power to the Riksdag of the Estates after authoritarian rule since 1772 on June 6th. 1810 is the year that peter Durand invented the tin can for preserving food. 1811 is the year that the Commissioners' Plan for Manhattan is presented on March 22nd. 1812 is the year that the last New Madrid Earthquake strikes New Madrid, Missouri, with an estimated moment magnitude of over 8; on February 7th. 1813 is the year that Gervasio Antonio de Posadas joins Argentina's second triumvirate on August 19th. 1814 is the year that Napoleon wins the Battle of Craonne on March 7th. 1815 is the year that the first Dutch student association, the Groninger Studenten Corps, Vindicat atque Polit is founded in the Netherlands on February 4th. 1816 is the year that Tsar Alexander I of Russia signs an order for the expulsion of the Jesuits from the Russian Empire on January 6th. 1817 is the year that Frédéric Cailliaud discovers the old Roman emerald mines at Sikait, Egypt on November 22nd. 1818 is the year that Carl III of Sweden-Norway is crowned king of Norway, in Trondheim on September 7th. 1819 is the year that the Carlsbad Decree is issued throughout the German Confederation on September 20th. 1820 is the year that Saint Cronan's Boys National School opens in Bray, Co. Wicklow, Ireland under the title Bray Male School on July 20th. 1821 is the year that the Philikí Etaireía are decisively defeated by the Ottomans at Drăgăşani (in Wallachia) on June 19th. 1822 is the year that Galileo Galilei's Dialogue is taken off the Index Librorum Prohibitorum, the Roman Catholic Church's list of banned books. 1823 is the year that Agustin de Iturbide, Emperor of Mexico,
